内容的主题。: 指示该书是否为精简版。
Indicates whether the book is an abridged edition.

内容的主题。: 简短描述。
An abstract is a short description that summarizes a CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 将车辆从给定的起始速度加速到给定的目标速度所需的时间。
The time needed to accelerate the vehicle from a given start velocity to a given target velocity.Typical unit code(s): SEC for secondsNote: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for seconds/0..100 km/h or seconds/0..60 mph. Simply use "SEC" for seconds and indicate the velocities in the name of the QuantitativeValue, or use valueReference with a QuantitativeValue of 0..60 mph or 0..100 km/h to specify the reference speeds.

内容的主题。: 通常在“问题/答案”站点上被接受为最佳的答案。
The answer(s) that has been accepted as best, typically on a Question/Answer site. Sites vary in their selection mechanisms, e.g. drawing on community opinion and/or the view of the Question author.

内容的主题。: 订单中包含的要约，例如产品、数量、价格组合。
The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.

内容的主题。: 卖方接受的付款方式。
The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.

内容的主题。: 指示食品企业是否接受预订。
Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be Boolean, an URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards compatibility) the strings Yes or No.

内容的主题。: 交付所需的密码，PIN码或访问码（例如，从储物柜中获取）。
Password, PIN, or access code needed for delivery (e.g. from a locker).

内容的主题。: 人的感官知觉系统或认知能力，通过它可以处理或感知信息。预期值包括：听觉，触觉，文本，视觉，colorDependent，chartOnVisual，chemOnVisual，diagramOnVisual，mathOnVisual，musicOnVisual，textOnVisual。
The human sensory perceptual system or cognitive faculty through which a person may process or perceive information. Expected values include: auditory, tactile, textual, visual, colorDependent, chartOnVisual, chemOnVisual, diagramOnVisual, mathOnVisual, musicOnVisual, textOnVisual.

内容的主题。: 足以理解资源所有知识内容的单个或组合accessMode的列表。期望值包括：听觉，触觉，文字，视觉。
A list of single or combined accessModes that are sufficient to understand all the intellectual content of a resource. Expected values include:  auditory, tactile, textual, visual.

内容的主题。: 指示资源与引用的可访问性API兼容（WebSchemas Wiki列出了可能的值）。
Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

内容的主题。: 标识足以完全控制所描述资源的输入法（WebSchemas Wiki列出了可能的值）。
Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

内容的主题。: 资源的内容功能，例如可访问的媒体，替代方法和受支持的可访问性增强功能（WebSchemas Wiki列出了可能的值）。
Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

内容的主题。: 所描述资源的特征对某些用户造成生理危险。与WCAG 2.0准则2.3有关（WebSchemas Wiki列出了可能的值）。
A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3 (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

内容的主题。: 与其他可访问性元数据一致的，特定于可访问性特征或缺陷的人类可读摘要，但表达了诸如“存在简短描述但非视觉用户将需要长描述”之类的微妙之处或“存在简短描述且没有长描述是必要的。”
A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as "short descriptions are present but long descriptions will be needed for non-visual users" or "short descriptions are present and no long descriptions are needed."

内容的主题。: 遵循房地产惯例的住宿类别，例如RESO（有关建议值，请参见PropertySubType和PropertyType字段）。
Category of an Accommodation, following real estate conventions e.g. RESO (see PropertySubType, and PropertyType fields for suggested values).

内容的主题。: 一些住宿的平面图。
A floorplan of some Accommodation.

内容的主题。: 付款将应用于的帐户的标识符。
The identifier for the account the payment will be applied to.

内容的主题。: 每月必须支付的最低金额。
A minimum amount that has to be paid in every month.

内容的主题。: 透支是指帐户达到零时从贷款机构获得的信贷的扩展。即使账户中没有资金，透支也可以使个人继续提取资金。基本上，银行允许人们借入一定数量的钱。
An overdraft is an extension of credit from a lending institution when an account reaches zero. An overdraft allows the individual to continue withdrawing money even if the account has no funds in it. Basically the bank allows people to borrow a set amount of money.

内容的主题。: 指定对CreativeWork负有法律责任的人。
Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 指示一个页面，其中记录了如何购买或以其他方式获得当前项目的许可证。
Indicates a page documenting how licenses can be purchased or otherwise acquired, for the current item.

内容的主题。: 购买产品的组织或个人。
The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

内容的主题。: ACRISS汽车分类代码是许多汽车租赁公司用于对车辆进行分类的代码。 ACRISS代表汽车租赁行业系统和标准协会。
The ACRISS Car Classification Code is a code used by many car rental companies, for classifying vehicles. ACRISS stands for Association of Car Rental Industry Systems and Standards.

内容的主题。: 执行一项操作必须满足的一组要求。如果指定了多个值，则满足一组要求将允许执行该操作。
A set of requirements that a must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action. If more than one value is specied, fulfilling one set of requirements will allow the Action to be performed.

内容的主题。: 可以完成请求的应用程序。
An application that can complete the request.

内容的主题。: 对象的子属性。这些选项受此操作的影响。
A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

内容的主题。: 可以针对给定URL执行操作的高级平台。要指定特定的应用程序或操作系统实例，请使用actionApplication。
The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.

内容的主题。: 指示操作的当前处置。
Indicates the current disposition of the Action.

内容的主题。: 对于NewsMediaOrganization或其他与新闻有关的组织，声明有关公众参与活动（对于新闻媒体，新闻编辑室而言）的声明，包括以数字方式或其他方式使公众参与出版物发布后的报道决策，报道和活动。
For a NewsMediaOrganization or other news-related Organization, a statement about public engagement activities (for news media, the newsroom’s), including involving the public - digitally or otherwise -- in coverage decisions, reporting and activities after publication.

内容的主题。: 活性成分，通常是化学化合物和/或生物物质。
An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

内容的主题。: 参加活动的时间长度。
Length of time to engage in the activity.

内容的主题。: 应该多久参加一次活动。
How often one should engage in the activity.

内容的主题。: 演员，例如电视，广播，电影，视频游戏等，或事件中。演员可以与单个项目或系列，剧集，剪辑关联。
An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: Clip, CreativeWorkSeason, Episode, Event, Movie, MovieSeries, RadioSeries, TVSeries, VideoGame, VideoGameSeries, VideoObject

内容的主题。: 演员，例如电视，广播，电影，视频游戏等中。演员可以与单个项目或系列，剧集，剪辑关联。
An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: Clip, Episode, Movie, MovieSeries, RadioSeries, TVSeries, VideoGame, VideoGameSeries, VideoObject

内容的主题。: 只能与第一个基本要约结合使用的额外要约（例如，可额外付费的补充和扩展）。
An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

内容的主题。: Person的其他名称可以用作中间名。
An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.

内容的主题。: 如果回答“是”，则是除了被邀请者之外还将参加的嘉宾人数。
If responding yes, the number of guests who will attend in addition to the invitee.

内容的主题。: 表示实体附加特征的属性值对，例如产品特性或schema.org中没有匹配属性的其他特性。注意：发布者应意识到，设计为使用特定schema.org属性（例如，宽度，颜色，gtin13等）的应用程序通常会期望这样的特性使用这些属性而不是使用通用属性/值机制提供的数据。
A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. width, color, gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

内容的主题。: 另一种类型，通常用于以微数据语法从外部词汇表中添加更多特定类型。这是事物与事物所在的类之间的关系。在RDFa语法中，最好对多个类型使用本机RDFa语法-'typeof'属性。 Schema.org工具可能对附加类型（尤其是那些在外部定义的类型）的了解较弱。
An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.

内容的主题。: 运动处方中可能需要与患者联系的任何其他组件。这可能包括锻炼顺序，重复运动的次数，定量距离，随着时间的推移等。
Any additional component of the exercise prescription that may need to be articulated to the patient. This may include the order of exercises, the number of repetitions of movement, quantitative distance, progressions over time, etc.
Physical address of the item.

内容的主题。: 国家。例如，美国。您还可以提供两个字母的ISO 3166-1 alpha-2国家/地区代码。
The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

内容的主题。: 街道地址所在的区域以及该区域中的位置。例如，山景城。
The locality in which the street address is, and which is in the region. For example, Mountain View.

内容的主题。: 所在地区和国家/地区中的地区。例如，加利福尼亚州或其他适当的一级行政区划
The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level Administrative division

内容的主题。: 可以施用该药物的途径，例如'口服'。
A route by which this drug may be administered, e.g. 'oral'.

内容的主题。: 从接受报价到实际使用资源或服务所需的时间。
The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

内容的主题。: 该疗法可能引起的并发症和/或副作用。如果已知不良后果是严重的（导致死亡，致残或永久损坏；需要住院；否则可能危及生命或需要立即就医），则将其标记为“ severeeAdverseOutcome”。
A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. If it is known that an adverse outcome is serious (resulting in death, disability, or permanent damage; requiring hospitalization; or is otherwise life-threatening or requires immediate medical attention), tag it as a seriouseAdverseOutcome instead.

内容的主题。: 影响测试结果的药物。
Drugs that affect the test's results.

内容的主题。: 此人所属的组织。 例如，学校/大学，俱乐部或团队。
An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.

内容的主题。: 执行此指示后代表情况的媒体对象。
A media object representing the circumstances after performing this direction.

内容的主题。: 动作的直接执行者或驱动者（有生命或无生命）。 例如 约翰写了一本书。
The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). e.g. John wrote a book.

内容的主题。: 该项目的总体评分（基于评论或评分的集合）。
The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: Brand, CreativeWork, Event, Offer, Organization, Place, Product, Service

内容的主题。: 飞机类型（例如“波音747”）。
The kind of aircraft (e.g., "Boeing 747").

内容的主题。: 音乐专辑。
A music album.

内容的主题。: 专辑按内容类型分类：配乐，现场专辑，录音室专辑等。
Classification of the album by it's type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

内容的主题。: 这张专辑的发行。
A release of this album.

内容的主题。: 该专辑的发行类型为：单张，EP或专辑。
The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

内容的主题。: 音乐专辑的集合。
A collection of music albums.

内容的主题。: 与服用该药物时饮酒有关的任何预防措施，指南，禁忌症等。
Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of alcohol while taking this drug.

内容的主题。: 计算分数所遵循的算法或规则。
The algorithm or rules to follow to compute the score.

内容的主题。: 学习资源和框架节点之间的对齐类别。 推荐值包括：“ requires”，“ textComplexity”，“ readingLevel”和“ educationalSubject”。
A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', and 'educationalSubject'.

内容的主题。: 项目的别名。
An alias for the item.

内容的主题。: CreativeWork的辅助标题。
A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 组织的校友。
Alumni of an organization.

内容的主题。: 该人是校友的组织。
An organization that the person is an alumni of.

内容的主题。: 住宿的便利设施特征（例如特色或服务）。 该通用属性不声明该功能是否包含在主要住宿的报价中，还是需要额外付费使用。
An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

内容的主题。: 金额。
The amount of money.

内容的主题。: 要约中包含的商品数量。
The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

内容的主题。: 表示与特别公告关联的特定CivicStructure或LocalBusiness。例如，特定的测试设施或营业时间特殊的企业。对于较大的地理区域，例如整个区域的隔离区，请使用spaceCoverage。
Indicates a specific CivicStructure or LocalBusiness associated with the SpecialAnnouncement. For example, a specific testing facility or business with special opening hours. For a larger geographic region like a quarantine of an entire region, use spatialCoverage.

内容的主题。: 借贷（或通过投资进行）收取的年利率，以单个百分比表示，表示贷款期限内实际的年度资金成本。这包括与交易相关的任何费用或额外费用。
The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.

内容的主题。: 该问题已收到的答案数量。
The number of answers this question has received.

内容的主题。: 抵消特定肌肉作用的肌肉。
The muscle whose action counteracts the specified muscle.

内容的主题。: 表示在某些CreativeWork中发生了声明。
Indicates an occurence of a Claim in some CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 状态适用的位置。
The location in which the status applies.

内容的主题。: 申请人可以申请的地点。这通常用于远程办公，而申请人不需要在物理办公室工作。注意：这不应用于公民身份或工作签证要求。
The location(s) applicants can apply from. This is usually used for telecommuting jobs where the applicant does not need to be in a physical office. Note: This should not be used for citizenship or work visa requirements.

内容的主题。: 可以完成请求的应用程序。
An application that can complete the request.

内容的主题。: 软件应用程序的类型，例如“游戏，多媒体”。
Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.

内容的主题。: 与该职位发布有关的更多信息的联系方式。
Contact details for further information relevant to this job posting.

内容的主题。: 程序停止为下一个注册周期收集应用程序的日期。
The date at which the program stops collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle.

内容的主题。: 程序开始为下一个注册周期收集应用程序的日期。
The date at which the program begins collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle.

内容的主题。: 应用程序的子类别，例如 “街机游戏”。
Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

内容的主题。: 该应用程序所属的应用程序套件的名称（例如Excel属于Office）。
The name of the application suite to which the application belongs (e.g. Excel belongs to Office).

内容的主题。: 适用送货费用或付款费用说明的送货方式。
The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

内容的主题。: 付款费用说明适用的付款方式。
The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.

内容的主题。: 由存档组织保存，保管或维护的收藏品，收藏品或项目。
Collection, fonds, or item held, kept or maintained by an ArchiveOrganization.

内容的主题。: 用户可以预期到达广播服务的区域。
The area within which users can expect to reach the broadcast service.

内容的主题。: 提供服务或提供的商品的地理区域。
The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: ContactPoint, DeliveryChargeSpecification, Demand, Offer, Organization, Service

内容的主题。: 航班终止的机场。
The airport where the flight terminates.

内容的主题。: 公共汽车到达的车站或车站。
The stop or station from which the bus arrives.

内容的主题。: 航班到达门的标识符。
Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.

内容的主题。: 火车到达的平台。
The platform where the train arrives.

内容的主题。: 火车旅行结束的车站。
The station where the train trip ends.

内容的主题。: 航班到达终端的标识符。
Identifier of the flight's arrival terminal.

内容的主题。: 预计到达时间。
The expected arrival time.

内容的主题。: 制作一件艺术品的多个副本时的副本数量-例如 对于限量发行20张的作品，“ artEdition”是指总份数（在此示例中为“ 20”）。
The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").

内容的主题。: 使用的材料。 （例如，油，水彩，丙烯酸，Linoprint，大理石，Cyanotype，数字，平版印刷，DryPoint，凹版印刷，粉彩，木刻，铅笔，混合介质等）
The material used. (e.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)

内容的主题。: 组成动脉结构的分支。
The branches that comprise the arterial structure.

内容的主题。: 例如绘画，绘画，雕塑，印刷，照片，组合，拼贴画等
e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.

内容的主题。: 文章的实际正文。
The actual body of the article.

内容的主题。: 文章可能属于杂志或报纸上的一个或多个“栏目”，例如“体育”，“生活方式”等。
Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.

内容的主题。: 除铅笔或数字线条艺术以外的其他媒介中作品的主要艺术家-例如，如果主要艺术品是用水彩或数字绘画完成的。
The primary artist for a work    in a medium other than pencils or digital line art--for example, if the    primary artwork is done in watercolors or digital paints.

内容的主题。: 艺术品的支撑材料，例如帆布，纸张，木材，木板等
The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

内容的主题。: 页面上考虑的医学实践方面，例如“诊断”，“治疗”，“原因”，“预后”，“病因”，“流行病学”等。
An aspect of medical practice that is considered on the page, such as 'diagnosis', 'treatment', 'causes', 'prognosis', 'etiology', 'epidemiology', etc.

内容的主题。: 库文件名，例如mscorlib.dll，system.web.dll。
Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

内容的主题。: 关联的产品/技术版本。例如.NET Framework 4.5。
Associated product/technology version. e.g., .NET Framework 4.5.

内容的主题。: 所描述的项目旨在评估所引用术语定义的能力或学习成果。
The item being described is intended to assess the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

内容的主题。: 与该实体关联的基础器官系统或结构的解剖结构。
The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.

内容的主题。: 与媒体对象关联的NewsArticle。
A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.

内容的主题。: 编码此CreativeWork的媒体对象。此属性是编码的同义词。
A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

内容的主题。: 如果适用，请描述与解剖系统相关的病理生理，包括系统的机械，物理和生化功能的潜在异常变化。
If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

内容的主题。: 担任运动队表演成员的人；运动员与教练相对的球员。
A person that acts as performing member of a sports team; a player as opposed to a coach.

内容的主题。: 参加活动的个人或组织。
A person or organization attending the event.

内容的主题。: 参加活动的人。
A person attending the event.

内容的主题。: 目标受众，即为其创建了某些内容的组。
An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: CreativeWork, Event, LodgingBusiness, PlayAction, Product, Service

内容的主题。: 与特定受众群体相关的目标群体（例如退伍军人，车主，音乐家等）。

The Organization responsible for authenticating the user's subscription. For example, many media apps require a cable/satellite provider to authenticate your subscription before playing media.

The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

内容的主题。: 要约的可用性：例如，有货，无货，预购等。
The availability of this item: for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.

The location in which the strength is available.

A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also inLanguage

Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

A medical service available from this provider.

内容的主题。: 药物的可用剂量强度。
An available dosage strength for the drug.

A diagnostic test or procedure offered by this lab.

After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.

内容的主题。: 此项所获得的或所赢得的奖项。
An award won by or for this item.

内容的主题。: 此项所获得的或所赢得的奖项。
Awards won by or for this item.

The away team in a sports event.

For an Article, typically a NewsArticle, the backstory property provides a textual summary giving a brief explanation of why and how an article was created. In a journalistic setting this could include information about reporting process, methods, interviews, data sources, etc.

The type of bed or beds included in the accommodation. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you use bed directly with a text.      If you want to indicate the quantity of a certain kind of bed, use an instance of BedDetails. For more detailed information, use the amenityFeature property.

内容的主题。: 在执行此指示之前代表环境的媒体对象。
A media object representing the circumstances before performing this direction.

内容的主题。: 一家经营受益人银行账户或为受益人释放资金的银行或分支机构，金融机构或国际金融机构
A bank or bank’s branch, financial institution or international financial institution operating the beneficiary’s bank account or releasing funds for the beneficiary

内容的主题。: 与工作相关的福利说明。
Description of benefits associated with the job.

The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.

内容的主题。: 订单的帐单地址。
The billing address for the order.

This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

The time interval used to compute the invoice.

The biomechanical properties of the bone.

内容的主题。: 出生日期。
Date of birth.

The place where the person was born.

内容的主题。: 媒体对象的比特率。
The bitrate of the media object.

内容的主题。: 此博客的一部分。
A posting that is part of this blog.

内容的主题。: 属于此博客的帖子。
The postings that are part of this blog.

内容的主题。: 将血液从心脏输送到肌肉的血管。
The blood vessel that carries blood from the heart to the muscle.

Location in the body of the anatomical structure.

Indicates the design and body style of the vehicle (e.g. station wagon, hatchback, etc.).

内容的主题。: 这本书的版本。
The edition of the book.

The format of the book.

'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.

内容的主题。: 预订的日期和时间。
The date and time the reservation was booked.

内容的主题。: 借物的人。
A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.

内容的主题。: 方框是由两点组成的矩形所包围的区域。第一点是下角，第二点是上角。方框表示为两个点，中间用空格隔开。
A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

内容的主题。: 从神经束中划出的分支。不要与branchOf混淆。
The branches that delineate from the nerve bundle. Not to be confused with branchOf.

内容的主题。: 简短的文本代码（也称为“商店代码”），用于唯一标识营业地点。该代码通常由parentOrganization分配，并在结构化URL中使用。例如，在URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047中，代码“ 3047”是一个特定的分支。
A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.For example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

内容的主题。: 该本地企业所属的较大组织（如果有）。不要与（解剖）分支混淆。
The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any. Not to be confused with (anatomical)branch.

内容的主题。: 与产品或服务相关的品牌，或由组织或业务人员维护的品牌。
The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

内容的主题。: 一组链接，可以帮助用户理解和浏览网站层次结构。
A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use by breastfeeding mothers.

The frequency in MHz for a particular broadcast.

The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.

The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).

The modulation (e.g. FM, AM, etc) used by a particular broadcast service

An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

内容的主题。: 用人类可读的文本指定浏览器要求。 例如，“需要HTML5支持”。
Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.

内容的主题。: 公交车的名称（例如Bolt Express）。
The name of the bus (e.g. Bolt Express).

The unique identifier for the bus.

Days of the week when the merchant typically operates, indicated via opening hours markup.

Defines the day(s) of the month on which a recurring Event takes place. Specified as an Integer between 1-31.

内容的主题。: 呼号，用于广播和无线电通信中以识别人员，无线电和电视台或车辆。
A callsign, as used in broadcasting and radio communications to identify people, radio and TV stations, or vehicles.

The number of calories.

CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: ActionAccessSpecification, Invoice, Offer, PhysicalActivity, Product, Recommendation, Service, SpecialAnnouncement

Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

A short textual code that uniquely identifies the value.

The coding system, e.g. 'ICD-10'.

A colleague of the person.

The number of items in the Collection.

The individual who adds color to inked drawings.

内容的主题。: 该CreativeWork收到的评论数（例如，文章，问题或答案）。这最适用于在带有注释系统的网站上发布的作品；其他注释可能存在于其他地方。

Specifying something physically contained by something else. Typically used here for the underlying anatomical structures, such as organs, that comprise the anatomical system.

内容的主题。: 影响项目可用性或访问方法的条件。通常用于现实世界中的物品，例如ArchiveOrganization拥有的ArchiveComponent。此属性不适合用作常规Web访问控制机制。它仅以自然语言表示。例如“可通过阅览室预约”或“仅可通过登录帐户访问”。
Conditions that affect the availability of, or method(s) of access to, an item. Typically used for real world items such as an ArchiveComponent held by an ArchiveOrganization. This property is not suitable for use as a general Web access control mechanism. It is expressed only in natural language.For example "Available by appointment from the Reading Room" or "Accessible only from logged-in accounts ".

内容的主题。: 收到确认给定订单或付款的号码。
A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

内容的主题。: 该结构所连接的其他解剖结构。
Other anatomical structures to which this structure is connected.

内容的主题。: 指示一个属性，该属性被用作约束，以针对与所指示类型相对应的实体集（通过populationType）定义StatisticsPopulation。
Indicates a property used as a constraint to define a StatisticalPopulation with respect to the set of entities  corresponding to an indicated type (via populationType).

内容的主题。: 此联系点上的选项（例如，免费电话或对有听力障碍的呼叫者的支持）。
An option available on this contact point (e.g. a toll-free number or support for hearing-impaired callers).

内容的主题。: 个人或组织的联系点。
A contact point for a person or organization.

内容的主题。: 个人或组织的联系点。
A contact point for a person or organization.

内容的主题。: 一个人或组织可以出于不同的目的而具有不同的联系点。 例如，销售联系点，PR联系点等。 此属性用于指定接触点的类型。
A person or organization can have different contact points, for different purposes. For example, a sales contact point, a PR contact point and so on. This property is used to specify the kind of contact point.

内容的主题。: 消费者使用RFID或NFC技术通过借记卡，信用卡或智能卡购买产品或服务的安全方法。
A secure method for consumers to purchase products or services via debit, credit or smartcards by using RFID or NFC technology.

内容的主题。: 地点与包含地点的地点之间的基本收容关系。
The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

内容的主题。: 地点与包含地点的地点之间的基本收容关系。
The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

内容的主题。: 一个地点与另一个地点之间的基本收容关系。
The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

内容的主题。: 属于媒体系列的一个季。
A season that is part of the media series.

内容的主题。: 内容中描述或描述的位置。 例如，照片或绘画中的位置。
The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

内容的主题。: 对内容的官方评级：例如“ MPAA PG-13”。
Official rating of a piece of content: for example,'MPAA PG-13'.

内容的主题。: 创意作品描述的特定时间，用于强调事件中特定时刻的作品（例如文章，视频对象等）。
The specific time described by a creative work, for works (e.g. articles, video objects etc.) that emphasise a particular moment within an Event.

内容的主题。: 文件大小（兆/千字节）。
File size in (mega/kilo) bytes.

内容的主题。: EntryPoint响应支持的内容类型。
The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

内容的主题。: 媒体对象的实际字节，例如图像文件或视频文件。
Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

内容的主题。: 该疗法的禁忌症。
A contraindication for this therapy.

内容的主题。: CreativeWork或Event的次要贡献者。
A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork or Event.

内容的主题。: 实际烹饪菜肴所需的时间，采用ISO 8601持续时间格式。
The time it takes to actually cook the dish, in ISO 8601 duration format.

内容的主题。: 烹饪方法，例如油炸，蒸，...
The method of cooking, such as Frying, Steaming, ...

内容的主题。: 拥有CreativeWork合法版权的一方。
The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 最初主张CreativeWork版权的年份。
The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

内容的主题。: 指示通过文本或其他文档中的CorrectionComment对CreativeWork的更正。
Indicates a correction to a CreativeWork, either via a CorrectionComment, textually or in another document.

内容的主题。: 对于一个组织（例如NewsMediaOrganization）而言，是一种描述（在新闻媒体中，新闻编辑室的）错误披露和纠正政策的声明。
For an Organization (e.g. NewsMediaOrganization), a statement describing (in news media, the newsroom’s) disclosure and correction policy for errors.

内容的主题。: 费用类别，例如批发，零售，报销上限等。
The category of cost, such as wholesale, retail, reimbursement cap, etc.

内容的主题。: 货币（用3个字母表示的药品费用。请参阅：http：//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217
The currency (in 3-letter of the drug cost. See: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217

内容的主题。: 成本数据来源的其他详细信息。 例如，“医疗保险B部分”。
Additional details to capture the origin of the cost data. For example, 'Medicare Part B'.

内容的主题。: 单位药物的成本。
The cost per unit of the drug.

内容的主题。: 不支持该应用程序的国家/地区。 您还可以提供两个字母的ISO 3166-1 alpha-2国家/地区代码。
Countries for which the application is not supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

内容的主题。: 支持该应用程序的国家。 您还可以提供两个字母的ISO 3166-1 alpha-2国家/地区代码。
Countries for which the application is supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

内容的主题。: 制作公司或负责电影或节目的个人的主要办事处所在的国家/地区。
The country of the principal offices of the production company or individual responsible for the movie or program.

内容的主题。: 采取此行动的过程。
A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

内容的主题。: 课程提供者使用的课程的标识符（例如CS101或6.001）。
The identifier for the Course used by the course provider (e.g. CS101 or 6.001).

内容的主题。: 课程实例或学习方式的传播媒介或手段，可以是文字标签（例如“在线”，“现场”或“混合”；“同步”或“异步”；“全日制”或“兼职”）或作为受控词汇表中术语的URL参考（例如https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous）。
The medium or means of delivery of the course instance or the mode of study, either as a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or as a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

内容的主题。: 参加课程的要求。可能是另一门课程的完成，也可能是文字说明，例如“教员许可”。需求可能是先决条件，要使用AlignmentObject进行引用。
Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another Course or a textual description like "permission of instructor". Requirements may be a pre-requisite competency, referenced using AlignmentObject.

内容的主题。: 参加该课程的学生的预期工作量，通常以每周或每月的数字提供，并且可以按类型细分。例如，“每周2个小时的讲座，1个小时的实验室工作和3个小时的独立学习”。
The amount of work expected of students taking the course, often provided as a figure per week or per month, and may be broken down by type. For example, "2 hours of lectures, 1 hour of lab work and 3 hours of independent study per week".

内容的主题。: 实时博客将停止报道活动的时间。请注意，活动结束后，报道可能会继续。
The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.

内容的主题。: 实时博客开始报道事件的时间。请注意，报道可能会在活动开始之前开始。还可以在开始覆盖之前创建LiveBlogPosting。
The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.

内容的主题。: 创意作品在生命周期中的阶段状态。示例术语包括不完整，草稿，已发布，已过时。一些组织为其发布生命周期的各个阶段定义了一组术语。
The status of a creative work in terms of its stage in a lifecycle. Example terms include Incomplete, Draft, Published, Obsolete. Some organizations define a set of terms for the stages of their publication lifecycle.

内容的主题。: 此CreativeWork的创建者/作者。这与CreativeWork的Author属性相同。
The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 描述的凭证的类别或类型，例如“学位”，“证书”，“徽章”或更具体的术语。
The category or type of credential being described, for example "degree”, “certificate”, “badge”, or more specific term.

内容的主题。: 如果发布者与byArtist不同，则将其归功于该组。
The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.

内容的主题。: CSS选择器，例如SpeakableSpecification或WebPageElement。在后一种情况下，页面内的多个匹配项可以构成一个概念上的“网页元素”。
A CSS selector, e.g. of a SpeakableSpecification or WebPageElement. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

内容的主题。: 接受的货币。使用标准格式：ISO 4217货币格式，例如“美元”;加密货币的股票代码“ BTC”；本地交易系统（LETS）和其他货币类型的知名名称“ Ithaca HOUR”。
The currency accepted.Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

内容的主题。: 表示货币金额的货币使用标准格式：ISO 4217货币格式，例如“美元”;加密货币的股票代码“ BTC”；本地交易系统（LETS）和其他货币类型的知名名称“ Ithaca HOUR”。
The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

内容的主题。: 货币的当前价格。
The current price of a currency.

内容的主题。: 下订单或支付发票的一方。
Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

内容的主题。: 订单截止时间允许商家描述他们将不再处理当天收到的订单的时间。对于在截止时间之后处理的订单，交货时间估计值将增加一天。最好通过ShippingRateSettings发布模式使用此属性。时间是使用ISO-8601 DateTime格式中的时间符号表示的，例如14：45：15Z将代表世界标准时间14：45h的每日截止时间。
Order cutoff time allows merchants to describe the time after which they will no longer process orders received on that day. For orders processed after cutoff time, one day gets added to the delivery time estimate. This property is expected to be most typically used via the ShippingRateSettings publication pattern. The time is indicated using the time notation from the ISO-8601 DateTime format, e.g.      14:45:15Z would represent a daily cutoff at 14:45h UTC.

内容的主题。: collectiondate-报告患者计数的日期。
collectiondate - Date for which patient counts are reported.

内容的主题。: 此数据记录适用的NHSN设施的县名称。使用cvdFacilityId标识设施。要提供其他详细信息，可以在医院条目上使用HealthcareReportingData。
Name of the County of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use cvdFacilityId to identify the facility. To provide other details, healthcareReportingData can be used on a Hospital entry.

内容的主题。: 该数据记录适用的NHSN设施的标识符。使用cvdFacilityCounty指示县。要提供其他详细信息，可以在医院条目上使用HealthcareReportingData。
Identifier of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use cvdFacilityCounty to indicate the county. To provide other details, healthcareReportingData can be used on a Hospital entry.

内容的主题。: 麻木床-医院急诊床：住院床，包括所有用于住院的配备人员的，有执照的和溢流（喘振）床。
numbeds - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BEDS: Inpatient beds, including all staffed, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients.

内容的主题。: numbedsocc-医院病床占用率：已占用的职员病床总数。
numbedsocc - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient beds that are occupied.

内容的主题。: numc19died-死亡：怀疑或确诊为COVID-19的患者在医院，急诊室或任何溢出地点死亡。
numc19died - DEATHS: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who died in the hospital, ED, or any overflow location.

内容的主题。: numc19hopats-医院发作：住院后14天或以上，在NHSN住院治疗地点住院的患者，其可疑或确诊的COVID-19发作。
numc19hopats - HOSPITAL ONSET: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location with onset of suspected or confirmed COVID-19 14 or more days after hospitalization.

内容的主题。: numc19hosppats-住院治疗：目前在住院治疗地点住院的怀疑或证实COVID-19的患者。
numc19hosppats - HOSPITALIZED: Patients currently hospitalized in an inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19.

关于: cvd C19怀疑或确诊且在呼吸机上的患者总数
内容的主题。: numc19mechventpats-住院和呼吸机：在NHSN住院治疗地点住院的怀疑或确诊COVID-19且在机械呼吸机上的患者。
numc19mechventpats - HOSPITALIZED and VENTILATED: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19 and are on a mechanical ventilator.

关于: cvd C19等待住院病床并在呼吸机上的可疑或确诊患者总数
内容的主题。: numc19ofmechventpats-ED /溢流和通气：处于ED或任何溢流位置等待住院病床并在机械呼吸机上的可疑或确诊COVID-19的患者。
numc19ofmechventpats - ED/OVERFLOW and VENTILATED: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed and on a mechanical ventilator.

内容的主题。: numc19overflowpats-ED /溢流：怀疑或确诊为COVID-19的患者在ED或等待住院床位的任何溢流位置。
numc19overflowpats - ED/OVERFLOW: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed.

内容的主题。: numicubeds-ICU床位：住院重症监护病房（ICU）床位总数。
numicubeds - ICU BEDS: Total number of staffed inpatient intensive care unit (ICU) beds.

内容的主题。: numicubedsocc-ICU床位：有人入住的ICU病床总数。
numicubedsocc - ICU BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient ICU beds that are occupied.

内容的主题。: numtotbeds（所有床位）-所有医院床位：所有住院和门诊床位的总数，包括所有用于医院或门诊病人的职员床，ICU，有执照的床和溢流（潮涌）床。
numtotbeds - ALL HOSPITAL BEDS: Total number of all Inpatient and outpatient beds, including all staffed,ICU, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients or outpatients.

内容的主题。: numvent-机械呼吸机：可用的呼吸机总数。
numvent - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS: Total number of ventilators available.

内容的主题。: numventuse-使用中的机械呼吸机：使用中的呼吸机总数。
numventuse - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS IN USE: Total number of ventilators in use.

内容的主题。: 数据Feed中的一项。 数据Feed可能包含许多元素。
An item within in a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

内容的主题。: 此目录中包含的数据集。
A dataset contained in this catalog.

内容的主题。: 数据集在时间上的适用范围，例如 对于2011年的人口普查数据集，则为2011年（采用ISO 8601时间间隔格式）。
The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

内容的主题。: 创建CreativeWork或将该项目添加到DataFeed的日期。
The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

内容的主题。: 从DataFeed中删除项目的日期时间。
The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

内容的主题。: 票证的发行日期。
The date the ticket was issued.

内容的主题。: 最近修改CreativeWork的日期或在DataFeed中修改条目的日期。
The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

内容的主题。: 在线列表的发布日期。
Publication date of an online listing.

内容的主题。: 首次广播/发布的日期。
Date of first broadcast/publication.

内容的主题。: 如果存在单个收件人，则收件人已阅读邮件的日期/时间。
The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.

内容的主题。: 如果存在单个收件人，则接收邮件的日期/时间。
The date/time the message was received if a single recipient exists.

内容的主题。: 发送消息的日期/时间。
The date/time at which the message was sent.

内容的主题。: 首次向相应的公共当局登记车辆的日期。
The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

内容的主题。: 日期行是新闻文章中的简短文本，描述了故事的撰写时间和地点，尽管该日期通常被省略。有时仅提供一个地名。还可以使用locationCreated（代表创建作品的位置，例如撰写新闻报道的位置）来更明确地表示与日期线相关的信息的结构化表示。对于在内容中描述或描述的位置，请使用contentLocation.Dateline摘要，其内容更多地是针对人类读者，而不是自动化处理，并且可能会有很大不同。例如：“黎巴嫩贝鲁特，6月2日”，“法国巴黎”，“ 2017年12月19日上午11:43从华盛顿报道”，“北京/莫斯科”，“菲律宾奎松市”。
A dateline is a brief piece of text included in news articles that describes where and when the story was written or filed though the date is often omitted. Sometimes only a placename is provided.Structured representations of dateline-related information can also be expressed more explicitly using locationCreated (which represents where a work was created e.g. where a news report was written).  For location depicted or described in the content, use contentLocation.Dateline summaries are oriented more towards human readers than towards automated processing, and can vary substantially. Some examples: "BEIRUT, Lebanon, June 2.", "Paris, France", "December 19, 2017 11:43AM Reporting from Washington", "Beijing/Moscow", "QUEZON CITY, Philippines".

内容的主题。: 这些开放时间在星期几有效。
The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

内容的主题。: 死亡日期。
Date of death.

内容的主题。: 该人死亡的地方。
The place where the person died.

内容的主题。: 输入的默认值。 对于需要文字的属性，默认值为文字值；对于需要对象的属性，默认值是对当前值之一的ID引用。
The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

内容的主题。: 目的地址。
Destination address.

内容的主题。: 如果交付方式是现场取货，则订单接收到货物离开仓库或准备取货之间的典型延迟。
The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

内容的主题。: 仪器的子属性。 交付方式。
A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

内容的主题。: 当包裹通过其旅程的每个环节（从装运到最终交付）时，都会添加新条目。
New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).

内容的主题。: 从收到订单到到达最终客户的货物之间的总延迟。
The total delay between the receipt of the order and the goods reaching the final customer.

内容的主题。: 组织与该组织的部门之间的关系，也称为组织（允许使用不同的URL，徽标，营业时间）。 例如：一家有药房的商店，或一家有咖啡厅的面包店。
A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

内容的主题。: 航班始发的机场。
The airport where the flight originates.

内容的主题。: 公共汽车出发的车站或车站。
The stop or station from which the bus departs.

内容的主题。: 航班登机口。
Identifier of the flight's departure gate.

内容的主题。: 火车出发的平台。
The platform from which the train departs.

内容的主题。: 火车出发的车站。
The station from which the train departs.

内容的主题。: 航班出发航站楼。
Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.

内容的主题。: 预计出发时间。
The expected departure time.

内容的主题。: 完成本文中的步骤所需的先决条件。
Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

内容的主题。: 项目的深度。
The depth of the item.

内容的主题。: 项目说明。
A description of the item.

内容的主题。: 运行该应用程序所需的设备。 在需要特定品牌/型号来运行应用程序的情况下使用。
Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

内容的主题。: 在差异诊断过程中将一个或多个替代条件视为诊断过程的输出。
One or more alternative conditions considered in the differential diagnosis process as output of a diagnosis process.

内容的主题。: 包含说明结构和/或其组件子结构和/或与其他结构的连接的图的图像。
An image containing a diagram that illustrates the structure and/or its component substructures and/or connections with other structures.

内容的主题。: 仪器的子属性。在此动作中使用的饮食。
A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

内容的主题。: 饮食计划特有的营养信息。可能包括饮食建议，包括应避免食用哪些食物，食用哪些食物以及与USDA或其他监管机构批准的饮食指南进行的特定更改/偏离。
Nutritional information specific to the dietary plan. May include dietary recommendations on what foods to avoid, what foods to consume, and specific alterations/deviations from the USDA or other regulatory body's approved dietary guidelines.

内容的主题。: 该病症的一组差异诊断之一。具体地，通常在认知过程中稍后考虑的密切相关或竞争性诊断，由此将这种医学状况与最有可能引起类似征兆和症状集合的其他疾病区分开，以达到患者的最简约诊断。
One of a set of differential diagnoses for the condition. Specifically, a closely-related or competing diagnosis typically considered later in the cognitive process whereby this medical condition is distinguished from others most likely responsible for a similar collection of signs and symptoms to reach the most parsimonious diagnosis or diagnoses in a patient.

内容的主题。: 电视，广播，电影，视频游戏等内容或事件。导演可以与单个项目或系列，剧集，剪辑关联。
A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: Clip, CreativeWorkSeason, Episode, Event, Movie, MovieSeries, RadioSeries, TVSeries, VideoGame, VideoGameSeries, VideoObject

内容的主题。: 电视，广播，电影，视频游戏等内容。导演可以与单个项目或系列，剧集，剪辑关联。
A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: Clip, Episode, Movie, MovieSeries, RadioSeries, TVSeries, VideoGame, VideoGameSeries, VideoObject

内容的主题。: 描述的子属性。该项目的简短描述，用于与其他类似项目进行区分。来自其他属性（尤其是名称）的信息可能对于使描述对消除歧义有用。
A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

内容的主题。: 任何折扣（适用于订单）。
Any discount applied (to an Order).

内容的主题。: 用于兑换折扣的代码。
Code used to redeem a discount.

内容的主题。: 折扣货币。使用标准格式：ISO 4217货币格式，例如“美元”;加密货币的股票代码“ BTC”；本地交易系统（LETS）和其他货币类型的知名名称“ Ithaca HOUR”。
The currency of the discount.Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

内容的主题。: 指定与UserComment关联的CreativeWork。
Specifies the CreativeWork associated with the UserComment.

内容的主题。: 指向包含CreativeWork注释的页面的链接。
A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 有关疾病预防的信息。
Information about disease prevention.

内容的主题。: 有关疾病传播的统计信息，可以是WebContent，也可以直接描述为数据集，也可以是数据集中的特定观察值。提供WebContent URL时，指示的页面可能还会包含更多此类标记。
Statistical information about the spread of a disease, either as WebContent, or  described directly as a Dataset, or the specific Observations in the dataset. When a WebContent URL is  provided, the page indicated might also contain more such markup.

内容的主题。: 该组织解散的日期。
The date that this organization was dissolved.

内容的主题。: 行驶的距离，例如锻炼或旅行。
The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

内容的主题。: 一组迹象和症状中的一个，可用于在鉴别诊断中将该诊断与其他诊断区分开。
One of a set of signs and symptoms that can be used to distinguish this diagnosis from others in the differential diagnosis.

内容的主题。: 该数据集的可下载形式，位于特定位置，特定格式。
A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format.

内容的主题。: 组织关于多样性政策的声明，例如一个NewsMediaOrganization。对于NewsMediaOrganization，是一份描述新闻室在人员配备和来源方面的多元化政策的声明，通常会提供人员配备数据。
Statement on diversity policy by an Organization e.g. a NewsMediaOrganization. For a NewsMediaOrganization, a statement describing the newsroom’s diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.

内容的主题。: 对于一个组织（通常但不一定是NewsMediaOrganization），有关人员配备多样性问题的报告。在新闻环境中，这可能是例如ASNE或RTDNA（US）的报道，或者是自我报道的。
For an Organization (often but not necessarily a NewsMediaOrganization), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.

内容的主题。: 进一步描述Web API的详细文档。
Further documentation describing the Web API in more detail.

内容的主题。: 指示作为OfferShippingDetails的一部分，何时不提供运送到特定的shippingDestination。
Indicates, as part of an OfferShippingDetails, when shipping to a particular shippingDestination is not available.

内容的主题。: 将属性与一个类联系在一起，该类是期望使用该属性的类型之一。
Relates a property to a class that is (one of) the type(s) the property is expected to be used on.

内容的主题。: 借款人是否是该物业所在司法管辖区的居民。
Whether borrower is a resident of the jurisdiction where the property is located.

内容的主题。: 时间准入将开始。
The time admission will commence.

内容的主题。: 可获得该药物/补充剂的剂型，例如 “药锭”，“悬浮液”，“注射剂”。
A dosage form in which this drug/supplement is available, e.g. 'tablet', 'suspension', 'injection'.

内容的主题。: 给定人群的药物给药方案，根据使用的类型，可以观察，推荐或最大剂量使用。
A dosing schedule for the drug for a given population, either observed, recommended, or maximum dose based on the type used.

内容的主题。: 剂量单位，例如 'mg'。
The unit of the dose, e.g. 'mg'.

内容的主题。: 剂量值，例如 500
The value of the dose, e.g. 500.

内容的主题。: 在购买昂贵的商品/服务开始时以现金支付的一种付款方式。 付款通常仅占全部购买价格的百分比。
a type of payment made in cash during the onset of the purchase of an expensive good/service. The payment typically represents only a percentage of the full purchase price.

内容的主题。: 如果可以下载文件，则下载二进制文件的URL。
If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

内容的主题。: 从社区收到对此问题，答案或评论的不赞成投票的人数。
The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

内容的主题。: 静脉排入的脉管系统。
The vasculature that the vein drains into.

内容的主题。: 驱动轮配置，即哪个车轮将通过传动系统从车辆的发动机接收扭矩。
The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

内容的主题。: 可以下车地点的地方。
Where a rental car can be dropped off.

内容的主题。: 可以下车地点时间。
When a rental car can be dropped off.

内容的主题。: 指定用药过程中使用的一种或多种药物
Specifying a drug or medicine used in a medication procedure

内容的主题。: 该药物所属的类别（例如他汀类药物）。
The class of drug this belongs to (e.g., statins).

内容的主题。: 测量药物的单位，例如 '5毫克片剂'。
The unit in which the drug is measured, e.g. '5 mg tablet'.

内容的主题。: Dun＆Bradstreet DUNS编号，用于标识组织或业务人员。
The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

内容的主题。: 一种重复或重叠的疗法。
A therapy that duplicates or overlaps this one.

内容的主题。: ISO 8601日期格式的项目（电影，音频录制，事件等）的持续时间。
The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in ISO 8601 date format.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: Audiobook, Event, MediaObject, Movie, MusicRecording, MusicRelease, QuantitativeValueDistribution, Schedule

内容的主题。: 保修承诺的期限。常见的unitCode值是ANN（年份），MON（月份）或DAY（天）。
The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

内容的主题。: 在执行此指示时代表环境的媒体对象。
A media object representing the circumstances while performing this direction.

内容的主题。: 在提前还清贷款的情况下应支付的罚款额。
The amount to be paid as a penalty in the event of early payment of the loan.

内容的主题。: 代表电影或电视作品的特定编辑/版本的EIDR（娱乐标识符注册表）标识符。例如，电影名称为“捉鬼敢死队”的电影，其标题EIDR为“ 10.5240 / 7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J” ”，进行了多次编辑，例如“ 10.5240 / 1F2A-E1C5-680A-14C6-E76B-I”和“ 10.5240 / 8A35-3BEE-6497-5D12-9E4F-3”。由于schema.org类型（例如电影和TVEpisode）可用于作品和它们的多个作品表达式，可以单独使用titleEIDR（用于一般说明），或与editEIDR一起使用以进行更具体的编辑说明。
An EIDR (Entertainment Identifier Registry) identifier representing a specific edit / edition for a work of film or television.For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" whose titleEIDR is "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J", has several edits e.g. "10.5240/1F2A-E1C5-680A-14C6-E76B-I" and "10.5240/8A35-3BEE-6497-5D12-9E4F-3".Since schema.org types like Movie and TVEpisode can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use titleEIDR alone (for a general description), or alongside editEIDR for a more edit-specific description.

内容的主题。: 指定编辑CreativeWork的人员。
Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 职位或职业所需的教育背景。
Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

内容的主题。: 与已建立的教育框架的一致性。如果可以使用简单的属性来描述一致性的性质，例如表示资源教或评估能力，则不应使用此属性。
An alignment to an established educational framework.This property should not be used where the nature of the alignment can be described using a simple property, for example to express that a resource teaches or assesses a competency.

内容的主题。: 成功完成本课程或课程后所获得的资格，奖励，证书，文凭或其他教育证书的说明。
A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other educational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

内容的主题。: 所描述的资源所面向的框架。
The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

内容的主题。: 通过教育或培训环境的进步程度。教育水平的示例包括“初学者”，“中级”或“高级”，以及正式的水平指标集。
The level in terms of progression through an educational or training context. Examples of educational levels include 'beginner', 'intermediate' or 'advanced', and formal sets of level indicators.

内容的主题。: 类似于courseMode，是整个程序的传递媒介或手段。该值可以是文本标签（例如“在线”，“现场”或“混合”；“同步”或“异步”；“全职”或“兼职”）或指向以下术语的URL引用受控词汇表（例如https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous）。
Similar to courseMode, The medium or means of delivery of the program as a whole. The value may either be a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

内容的主题。: 教育受众的教育角色。
An educationalRole of an EducationalAudience.

内容的主题。: 教育背景下的工作目的；例如“任务”，“小组工作”。
The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

内容的主题。: 位置的高程（WGS 84）。值的形式可以是“数字计量单位”（例如“ 1,000 m”，“ 3,200 ft”），而数字本身应被视为以米为单位的值。
The elevation of a location (WGS 84). Values may be of the form 'NUMBER UNIT OF MEASUREMENT' (e.g., '1,000 m', '3,200 ft') while numbers alone should be assumed to be a value in meters.

内容的主题。: 这项工作的申请人需要的法律要求，例如公民身份，签证和其他文件。
The legal requirements such as citizenship, visa and other documentation required for an applicant to this job.

内容的主题。: 给定报价对其有效的客户类型。
The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

内容的主题。: 给定报价有效的持续时间。
The duration for which the given offer is valid.

内容的主题。: 要约或价格规格有效的订购数量的间隔和度量单位。这允许例如指定一定的运费仅对一定数量有效。
The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

内容的主题。: ISO 3166-1（ISO 3166-1 alpha-2）或ISO 3166-2代码，地方或地理形状的地缘政治区域的要约或交付费用规范有效。另请参见ineligibleRegion 。
The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.See also ineligibleRegion.

内容的主题。: 要约或价格说明对其有效的货币单位的交易量，例如用于表示最小购买量，表示超过一定订购量的免费送货或将接受信用卡的购买限制在一定的最小量。
The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

内容的主题。: 电子邮件地址。
Email address.

内容的主题。: 指向特定视频播放器的URL。通常，这是embed标签的src元素中的信息，不应与loc标签的内容相同。
A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the src element of an embed tag and should not be the same as the content of the loc tag.

内容的主题。: 二氧化碳排放量（克/公里）。当与QuantitativeValue结合使用时，请将“ g / km”放入该值的unitText属性中，因为没有针对“ g / km”的UN / CEFACT通用代码。
The CO2 emissions in g/km. When used in combination with a QuantitativeValue, put "g/km" into the unitText property of that value, since there is no UN/CEFACT Common Code for "g/km".

内容的主题。: 为该组织工作的人。
Someone working for this organization.

内容的主题。: 在该组织工作的人。
People working for this organization.

内容的主题。: 对该职位的雇主，职业机会和工作环境的描述。
A description of the employer, career opportunities and work environment for this position.

内容的主题。: 就业类型（例如，全职，兼职，合同，临时，季节性，实习）。
Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).

内容的主题。: 指示员工报告和/或要在其中执行工作的部门，部门和/或设施。
Indicates the department, unit and/or facility where the employee reports and/or in which the job is to be performed.

内容的主题。: 此媒体对象编码的CreativeWork。
The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

内容的主题。: 编码此CreativeWork的媒体对象。此属性是associatedMedia的同义词。
A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

内容的主题。: 通常使用MIME格式表示的媒体类型（请参阅IANA网站和MDN参考），例如如果是CreativeWork具有多个媒体类型表示形式，则可以使用编码来指示每个MediaObject以及特定的encodingFormat信息。未注册或适当位置的编码和文件格式可以而是通过最合适的URL来表示，例如定义网页或Wikipedia / Wikidata条目。
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see IANA site and MDN reference) e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.).In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, encoding can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular encodingFormat information.Unregistered or niche encoding and file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia/Wikidata entry.

内容的主题。: EntryPoint请求支持的编码类型。
The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.

内容的主题。: 编码此CreativeWork的媒体对象。
A media object that encodes this CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 项目的结束日期和时间（采用ISO 8601日期格式）。
The end date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: CreativeWorkSeason, CreativeWorkSeries, DatedMoneySpecification, EducationalOccupationalProgram, Event, Role, Schedule

内容的主题。: 剪辑的结束时间表示为从工作开始起的秒数。
The end time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

内容的主题。: 结束时间。对于保留的事件或服务（例如FoodFoundationReservation），预计结束时间。对于跨越一段时间的操作，执行操作的时间。例如约翰从一月到十二月写了一本书。对于包括音频和视频在内的媒体，它是较大文件中剪辑结尾的时间偏移。请注意，即使使用时间描述日期，Event也会使用startDate / endDate而不是startTime / endTime。在将来的修订版中可能会澄清这种情况。
The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to December. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the end of a clip within a larger file.Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

内容的主题。: 参与者的子属性。受支持的人员/组织。
A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

内容的主题。: 支持该计划的人员或组织。
People or organizations that endorse the plan.

内容的主题。: 内燃机气缸内所有活塞以单次运动扫过的体积。典型单位代码：CMQ表示立方厘米，LTR表示升，INQ表示立方英寸*注1：您可以链接到有关如何使用valueReference属性确定给定值的信息。*注2：您可以使用minValue和maxValue表示范围。
The volume swept by all of the pistons inside the cylinders of an internal combustion engine in a single movement. Typical unit code(s): CMQ for cubic centimeter, LTR for liters, INQ for cubic inches* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the valueReference property.* Note 2: You can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.

内容的主题。: 车辆发动机的功率。典型的单位代码：KWT（千瓦），BHP（制动马力），N12（公制马力）（PS，1 PS = 735,49875 W）注1：测量发动机功率的方法有很多。
The power of the vehicle's engine.    Typical unit code(s): KWT for kilowatt, BHP for brake horsepower, N12 for metric horsepower (PS, with 1 PS = 735,49875 W)Note 1: There are many different ways of measuring an engine's power.

内容的主题。: 为车辆提供动力的发动机类型。
The type of engine or engines powering the vehicle.

内容的主题。: 位置的子属性。发生该行为的娱乐业务。
A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.

内容的主题。: 相关患者的特征，例如年龄，性别，种族等。
The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

内容的主题。: 电视连续剧或季节中电视，广播或游戏媒体的一集。
An episode of a tv, radio or game media within a series or season.

内容的主题。: 情节在情节的有序组中的位置。
Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.

内容的主题。: 电视/电台系列或季节的一集。
An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

内容的主题。: 定性值的这种排序关系表明主体等于客体。
This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

内容的主题。: 对于失败的操作，请提供有关失败原因的更多信息。
For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure.

内容的主题。: 执行说明时估计的一个或多个耗材的成本。
The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.

内容的主题。: 预计飞行时间。
The estimated time the flight will take.

内容的主题。: 基于各种变量（包括但不限于行业，职位和位置）的职位发布或职业的估计薪水。估计工资通常是由外部组织而不是雇用组织计算的，后者可能未承诺估计价值。
An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

内容的主题。: 估计其风险的情况，并发症或症状。
The condition, complication, or symptom whose risk is being estimated.

内容的主题。: 关于道德政策的声明，例如有关新闻和出版惯例的NewsMediaOrganization或“餐厅”中描述食物来源政策的页面。就NewsMediaOrganization而言，ethicsPolicy通常是一种描述组织期望的个人，组织和公司行为标准的声明。
Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a NewsMediaOrganization regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a Restaurant, a page describing food source policies. In the case of a NewsMediaOrganization, an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.

内容的主题。: 与该地点，组织或动作相关的即将发生或过去的事件。
Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: InformAction, InviteAction, JoinAction, LeaveAction, Organization, Place, PlayAction

内容的主题。: 事件的eventAttendanceMode指示事件是在线，离线还是混合发生。
The eventAttendanceMode of an event indicates whether it occurs online, offline, or a mix.

内容的主题。: 将事件与时间表关联。在某些情况下，最好是共享一系列重复事件的时间表，而不是共享各个事件本身的数据。例如，网站或应用程序可能更愿意发布每周体育课的时间表，而不是提供每个事件的数据。时间表可以由应用程序处理，以将即将发生的事件添加到日历中。与使用此属性的计划相关联的事件不应具有startDate或endDate属性。这些是在关联的计划中定义的，从而避免了使用数据的客户端的任何歧义。该属性可能具有重复的值以指定不同的时间表，例如不同的月份或季节。
Associates an Event with a Schedule. There are circumstances where it is preferable to share a schedule for a series of repeating events rather than data on the individual events themselves. For example, a website or application might prefer to publish a schedule for a weekly      gym class rather than provide data on every event. A schedule could be processed by applications to add forthcoming events to a calendar. An Event that      is associated with a Schedule using this property should not have startDate or endDate properties. These are instead defined within the associated Schedule, this avoids any ambiguity for clients using the data. The property might have repeated values to specify different schedules, e.g. for different months      or seasons.

内容的主题。: 事件的eventStatus表示其状态；当事件被取消或重新安排时特别有用。
An eventStatus of an event represents its status; particularly useful when an event is cancelled or rescheduled.

内容的主题。: 与这个地点或组织相关的即将发生或过去的事件。
Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

内容的主题。: 用于制定指南的数据的证据强度（列举）。
Strength of evidence of the data used to formulate the guideline (enumerated).

内容的主题。: 用于制定指南的数据来源，例如RCT，共识意见等。
Source of the data used to formulate the guidance, e.g. RCT, consensus opinion, etc.

内容的主题。: 该作品是一个示例/实例/实现/派生的创造性作品。
A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.

内容的主题。: 定义日期或日期时间，在该日期或日期时间期间不会发生预定事件。该属性允许指定排定的例外。如果将异常指定为DateTime，则仅应将在该特定日期和时间开始的事件排除在计划之外。如果将异常指定为“日期”，则应将排定在该24小时内安排的任何事件排除在排定之外。这样一整天都可以从日程安排中排除，而不必逐项逐项列出事件。
Defines a Date or DateTime during which a scheduled Event will not take place. The property allows exceptions to      a Schedule to be specified. If an exception is specified as a DateTime then only the event that would have started at that specific date and time      should be excluded from the schedule. If an exception is specified as a Date then any event that is scheduled for that 24 hour period should be      excluded from the schedule. This allows a whole day to be excluded from the schedule without having to itemise every scheduled event.

内容的主题。: 经纪人或其他中间人买卖外币的价格之间的差额。
The difference between the price at which a broker or other intermediary buys and sells foreign currency.

内容的主题。: 库文件名，例如mscorlib.dll，system.web.dll。
Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

内容的主题。: 位置的子属性。采取此行动的过程。
A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

内容的主题。: 仪器的子属性。此动作使用的锻炼计划。
A sub property of instrument. The exercise plan used on this action.

内容的主题。: 仪器的子属性。在此动作中使用的饮食。
A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

内容的主题。: 运动或活动的类型，例如力量训练，柔韧性训练，有氧运动，心脏康复等。
Type(s) of exercise or activity, such as strength training, flexibility training, aerobics, cardiac rehabilitation, etc.

内容的主题。: 此对象的exif数据。
exif data for this object.

内容的主题。: 包裹最早到达的日期。
The earliest date the package may arrive.

内容的主题。: 包裹可能到达的最晚日期。
The latest date the package may arrive.

内容的主题。: 在短期或长期的医疗条件下可能出现的结果。
The likely outcome in either the short term or long term of the medical condition.

内容的主题。: 在用户执行操作之前必须接受的要约。 例如，用户可能需要先购买电影才能观看它。
An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.

内容的主题。: 描述该职位或职业所需的技能和经验。
Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

内容的主题。: 与计划有关的医学专家建议。
Medical expert advice related to the plan.

内容的主题。: 内容过期的日期，不再有用或不可用。 例如，其可用性或相关性是有时间限制的VideoObject或NewsArticle，或者其发布者希望表明它在某个日期之后可能不再相关（或有助于突出显示）的ClaimReview事实检查。
Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a VideoObject or NewsArticle whose availability or relevance is time-limited, or a ClaimReview fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date.

内容的主题。: 姓。 在美国，人员的姓氏。 可以与namedName一起使用，而不是name属性。
Family name. In the U.S., the last name of an Person. This can be used along with givenName instead of the name property.

内容的主题。: 脂肪克数。
The number of grams of fat.

内容的主题。: 传真号码。
The fax number.

内容的主题。: 此应用程序提供的功能或模块（其他应用程序可能需要）。
Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).

内容的主题。: 适用于一类金融产品或金融服务组织的费用，佣金和其他术语的描述。
Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.

内容的主题。: 纤维克数。
The number of grams of fiber.

内容的主题。: 媒体类型，通常是内容的MIME格式（请参阅IANA网站），例如SoftwareApplication二进制文件的application / zip。在CreativeWork具有多个媒体类型表示形式的情况下，可以使用“编码”指示每个MediaObject以及特定的文件格式信息。可以通过最合适的网址（例如，定义网页或Wikipedia条目。
Media type, typically MIME format (see IANA site) of the content e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information. Unregistered or niche file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia entry.

内容的主题。: 应用程序/程序包的大小（例如18MB）。在没有单位（MB，KB等）的情况下，将假定为KB。
Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.

内容的主题。: 学生可以用来支付与该计划相关的学费或费用的经济援助类型或计划。
A financial aid type or program which students may use to pay for tuition or fees associated with the program.

内容的主题。: 指示在某些CreativeWork中首次出现索赔的情况。
Indicates the first known occurence of a Claim in some CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 首次执行工作的日期和地点。
The date and place the work was first performed.

内容的主题。: 飞行距离。
The distance of the flight.

内容的主题。: 航班的唯一标识符，包括航空公司的IATA代码。例如，如果描述美联航航班110，其中美联航的IATA代码为“ UA”，则flightNumber为“ UA110”。
The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.

内容的主题。: 多层建筑物中的住宿楼层。由于计数系统在国际上有所不同，因此应尽可能使用本地系统。
The floor level for an Accommodation in a multi-storey building. Since counting  systems vary internationally, the local system should be used where possible.

内容的主题。: 下限是必须授权信用卡交易的金额。
A floor limit is the amount of money above which credit card transactions must be authorized.

内容的主题。: 住宿的大小，例如典型单位代码：MTK（平方米），FTK（平方英尺）或YDK（平方码）
The size of the accommodation, e.g. in square meter or squarefoot.Typical unit code(s): MTK for square meter, FTK for square foot, or YDK for square yard

内容的主题。: 对象的子属性。被关注的个人或组织。
A sub property of object. The person or organization being followed.

内容的主题。: 最通用的单向社会关系。
The most generic uni-directional social relation.

内容的主题。: 执行该程序后的典型或建议的后续护理。
Typical or recommended followup care after the procedure is performed.

内容的主题。: 位置的子属性。采取行动的特定食品机构。
A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.

内容的主题。: 位置的子属性。采取行动的特定食品事件。
A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

内容的主题。: 与服用该药物时食用特定食品有关的任何预防措施，指南，禁忌症等。
Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of specific foods while taking this drug.

内容的主题。: 创建这个组织的人。
A person who founded this organization.

内容的主题。: 创建这个组织的人。
A person who founded this organization.

内容的主题。: 该组织成立的日期。
The date that this organization was founded.

内容的主题。: 本组织成立的地方。
The place where the Organization was founded.

内容的主题。: 一个标志，指示可以免费访问该项目，事件或地点。
A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

内容的主题。: 高于（或等于）运费的货币价值。旨在通过OfferShippingSpecification与与该ShippingSettings匹配的shippingSettingsLink一起使用。
A monetary value above which (or equal to) the shipping rate becomes free. Intended to be used via an OfferShippingSpecification with shippingSettingsLink matching this ShippingSettings.

内容的主题。: 多长时间服用一次，例如'日常'。
How often the dose is taken, e.g. 'daily'.

内容的主题。: 位置的子属性。操作前对象或代理的原始位置。
A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

内容的主题。: 油箱的容量，如果是电动汽车，则为电池的容量。如果要存储的组件有多个，则应指示所有相同类型的存储的总和。典型单位代码：LTR（升），GLL（美国加仑），GLI（英国/英制加仑），AMH（安培小时）（用于电动汽车）。
The capacity of the fuel tank or in the case of electric cars, the battery. If there are multiple components for storage, this should indicate the total of all storage of the same type.Typical unit code(s): LTR for liters, GLL of US gallons, GLI for UK / imperial gallons, AMH for ampere-hours (for electrical vehicles).

内容的主题。: 对于给定的车辆，在特定距离或时间段内行驶所消耗的燃油量（例如，每100公里的公升）。注1：不幸的是，没有每100公里公升的标准单位代码。使用unitText表示度量单位，例如L / 100 km。注2：有两种指示燃油消耗的方法，即燃油消耗量（例如每100公里8升）和燃油效率（例如每加仑30英里）。注意：通常，绝对值仅在与行驶速度（“以80 km / h”行驶）或使用方式（“城市交通”）相关时才有用。您可以使用valueReference将燃油消耗的值链接到另一个值。
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km.  Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.

内容的主题。: 每单位燃料使用的距离；最常见的是英里/加仑（mpg）或公里/升（km / L）。注1：不幸的是，没有标准的单位代码来表示英里/加仑或公里/升。使用unitText表示度量单位，例如mpg或km / L。注2：有两种指示燃油消耗的方式，即耗油量（例如，每100公里8升）和燃油效率（例如，每加仑30英里）。注意：通常，绝对值仅在与行驶速度（“以80 km / h”行驶）或使用方式（“城市交通”）相关时才有用。您可以使用valueReference将燃油经济性的值链接到另一个值。
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.

内容的主题。: 适用于车辆发动机的燃料类型。如果车辆只有一个引擎，则可以将该属性直接附加到车辆上。
The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.

内容的主题。: 关节允许的活动度。
The degree of mobility the joint allows.

内容的主题。: 表示通过赠款资助或赞助的项目。
Indicates an item funded or sponsored through a Grant.

内容的主题。: 通过某种财政捐助来支持（赞助人）某物的个人或组织。
A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

内容的主题。: 在此服务器上播放的视频游戏。
Video game which is played on this server.

内容的主题。: 物品是游戏世界中的一个对象，可以由玩家或非玩家角色收集。
An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

内容的主题。: 游戏（或游戏的一部分）的真实或虚构位置。
Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

内容的主题。: 用于玩视频游戏的电子系统。
The electronic systems used to play video games.

内容的主题。: 可以在其上玩游戏的服务器。
The server on which  it is possible to play the game.

内容的主题。: 链接到技巧，策略等
Links to tips, tactics, etc.

内容的主题。: 某物的性别，通常是人，但也可能是虚构人物，动物等。虽然可以使用公母，但对于不标识为二进制性别的人，文本字符串也是可以接受的。性别属性也可以扩展使用，以涵盖例如运动队的性别。与个人性别一样，我们不会尝试列举所有可能性。混合性别的SportsTeam可以使用文本值“混合”来表示。
Gender of something, typically a Person, but possibly also fictional characters, animals, etc. While Male and Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who do not identify as a binary gender. The gender property can also be used in an extended sense to cover e.g. the gender of sports teams. As with the gender of individuals, we do not try to enumerate all possibilities. A mixed-gender SportsTeam can be indicated with a text value of "Mixed".

内容的主题。: 创意作品，广播频道或组的类型。
Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

内容的主题。: 地点的地理坐标。
The geo coordinates of the place.

内容的主题。: 表示两个几何（或其表示的位置）之间的关系，将包含的几何与包含的几何相关联。 “ a包含b，只要b的点不位于a的外部，而b的内部的至少一个点位于a的内部”。如DE-9IM中所定义。
Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in DE-9IM.

内容的主题。: 表示两个几何（或其代表的位置）之间的关系，将一个几何与另一个覆盖它的几何相关。如DE-9IM中所定义。
Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in DE-9IM.

内容的主题。: 表示两个几何（或其表示的位置）之间的关系，将覆盖几何与覆盖几何相关联。 “ b的每个点都是a的点（内部或边界）”。如DE-9IM中所定义。
Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in DE-9IM.

内容的主题。: 表示两个几何图形（或它们表示的位置）之间的关系，将一个几何图形与另一个与其交叉的几何图形相关联：“ a交叉b：它们具有一些但不是全部内部点相同，并且交点的尺寸小于交点的尺寸至少其中之一”。如DE-9IM中所定义。
Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in DE-9IM.

内容的主题。: 表示两个几何（或它们代表的位置）在拓扑上不相交的空间关系：它们没有共同点。它们形成了一组不连续的几何。”（对称关系，在DE-9IM中定义）
Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM)

内容的主题。: 表示空间关系，其中两个几何（或其表示的位置）在拓扑上相等，如DE-9IM中所定义。 “如果两个几何的内部相交并且一个几何的内部或边界的任何部分都不与另一个几何的外部相交，则两个拓扑在拓扑上相等”（对称关系）
Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in DE-9IM. "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship)

内容的主题。: 表示两个几何（或其表示的位置）至少有一个共同点的空间关系。如DE-9IM中所定义。
Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in DE-9IM.

内容的主题。: 指示位于GeoShape中心的GeoCoordinates，例如GeoCircle。
Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape e.g. GeoCircle.

内容的主题。: 表示两个几何图形（或它们表示的位置）之间的关系，将一个几何图形与另一个在地理空间上重叠的几何图形相关联，即它们具有一些但并非全部相同的点。如DE-9IM中所定义。
Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in DE-9IM.

内容的主题。: 表示一个GeoCircle的近似半径（米，除非通过“距离”符号另外指出）。
Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

内容的主题。: 表示两个几何（或它们代表的位置）接触的空间关系：它们至少有一个共同的边界点，但没有内部点。”（对称关系，如DE-9IM所定义）
Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM )

内容的主题。: 表示两个几何图形（或它们表示的位置）之间的关系，将一个几何图形与包含该几何图形的一个几何图形相关联，即它位于其内部（即内部）。如DE-9IM中所定义。
Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in DE-9IM.

内容的主题。: 与受众群体相关联的地理区域。
The geographic area associated with the audience.

内容的主题。: 有关进行测试的信息（针对“医疗条件”），例如在大流行的情况下。
Information about getting tested (for a MedicalCondition), e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

内容的主题。: 给定的名称。在美国，人的名字。它可以与familyName一起使用，而不是name属性。
Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person. This can be used along with familyName instead of the name property.

内容的主题。: 各个组织，个人或地点的全球位置编号（GLN，有时也称为国际位置编号或ILN）。 GLN是一个13位数字，用于标识各方和实际位置。
The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

内容的主题。: GovernmentBenefitsInfo提供有关与特殊公告相关的政府收益的信息。
governmentBenefitsInfo provides information about government benefits associated with a SpecialAnnouncement.

内容的主题。: 在任何到期日之后，借款人必须履行其义务才能视为发生违约（未付款）的时间段。
The period of time after any due date that the borrower has to fulfil its obligations before a default (failure to pay) is deemed to have occurred.

内容的主题。: 被授予此权限的个人，组织，联系点或受众。
The person, organization, contact point, or audience that has been granted this permission.

内容的主题。: 定性值的这种排序关系表明主题大于主题。
This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.

内容的主题。: 定性值的这种排序关系表明主题大于或等于对象。
This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.

内容的主题。: 全球贸易商品编号（GTIN）。 GTIN使用数字识别码识别贸易项，包括产品和服务。 gtin属性概括了较早的gtin8，gtin12，gtin13和gtin14属性。 GS1数字链接规范将GTIN表示为URL。正确的gtin值应该是有效的GTIN，这意味着它应该是8、12、13或14位数字的全数字字符串，或者是基于该字符串的“ GS1数字链接” URL。数字组件还应具有有效的GS1校验位，并满足有效GTIN的其他规则。另请参阅GS1的GTIN摘要和维基百科。不需要或不建议使用gtin值的左填充。
A Global Trade Item Number (GTIN). GTINs identify trade items, including products and services, using numeric identification codes. The gtin property generalizes the earlier gtin8, gtin12, gtin13, and gtin14 properties. The GS1 digital link specifications express GTINs as URLs. A correct gtin value should be a valid GTIN, which means that it should be an all-numeric string of either 8, 12, 13 or 14 digits, or a "GS1 Digital Link" URL based on such a string. The numeric component should also have a valid GS1 check digit and meet the other rules for valid GTINs. See also GS1's GTIN Summary and Wikipedia for more details. Left-padding of the gtin values is not required or encouraged.

内容的主题。: 产品或报价所引用产品的GTIN-12代码。 GTIN-12是由U.P.C.组成的12位GS1识别码。用于识别贸易项目的公司前缀，项目参考和校验位。有关更多详细信息，请参见GS1 GTIN摘要。
The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

内容的主题。: 产品或报价所引用产品的GTIN-13代码。这等效于13位ISBN码和EAN UCC-13。只需添加前面的零，就可以将以前的12位UPC码转换为GTIN-13码。有关更多详细信息，请参见GS1 GTIN摘要。
The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceeding zero. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

内容的主题。: 产品或报价所涉及产品的GTIN-14代码。有关更多详细信息，请参见GS1 GTIN摘要。
The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

内容的主题。: 产品或报价所引用产品的GTIN-8代码。此代码也称为EAN / UCC-8或8位EAN。有关更多详细信息，请参见GS1 GTIN摘要。
The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

内容的主题。: 所有可用报价中的最高价格。 使用准则：使用0123456789（Unicode'DIGIT ZERO'（U + 0030）到'DIGIT NINE'（U + 0039））中的值，而不是表面上类似的Unicode符号。 （Unicode'FULL STOP'（U + 002E））而不是'，'表示小数点。 避免将这些符号用作可读性分隔符。
