内容的主题。: 3DModel是否允许调整大小。例如，房间布局应用程序通常不允许调整3DModel元素的大小以反映现实。
Whether the 3DModel allows resizing. For example, room layout applications often do not allow 3DModel elements to be resized to reflect reality.

内容的主题。: 指向另一个功能相似的产品（或多个产品）的指针。
A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

内容的主题。: 可以将其标记为“ true”，以表示当某些设置中的shippingSettingsLink引用了某些已发布的ShippingRateSettings打算应用于同一商家发布的所有OfferShippingDetails时。将此属性的true值与shippingLabel一起使用是没有意义的，因为此属性与未标记的ShippingRateSettings一起使用。
This can be marked 'true' to indicate that some published ShippingRateSettings are intended to apply to all OfferShippingDetails published by the same merchant, when referenced by a shippingSettingsLink in those settings. It is not meaningful to use a 'true' value for this property alongside a shippingLabel, since this property is for use with unlabelled ShippingRateSettings.

内容的主题。: 指向基础产品的指针，该产品是该产品的变体。可以安全地推断出，该变体会继承基本模型的所有产品功能，除非在本地定义。这不是传递的。
A pointer to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive.

内容的主题。: 本书的ISBN。
The ISBN of the book.

内容的主题。: 所有经济活动的国际工业分类标准（ISIC）修订版4，针对特定组织，业务人员或地点。
The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

内容的主题。: 用于记录的国际标准记录代码。
The International Standard Recording Code for the recording.

内容的主题。: 标识此序列出版物的国际标准序列号（ISSN）。您可以重复此属性以标识此串行出版物的不同格式或链接的ISSN（ISSN-L）。
The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

内容的主题。: 标识发布问题；例如“ iii”或“ 2”。
Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".

内容的主题。: 签发票证或许可证的组织。
The organization issuing the ticket or permit.

内容的主题。: 获得许可的服务被授予。
The service through with the permit was granted.

内容的主题。: 该作品的国际标准音乐作品规范。
The International Standard Musical Work Code for the composition.

内容的主题。: 列表或数据Feed中的条目所代表的实体（例如“艺术家”列表中的“艺术家”）。
An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists')’.

内容的主题。: OfferItemCondition中的预定义值或产品或服务或要约中包含的产品或服务的条件的文字说明。
A predefined value from OfferItemCondition or a textual description of the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer.

内容的主题。: 对于itemListElement值，可以使用简单的字符串（例如“ Peter”，“ Paul”，“ Mary”），现有实体或使用ListItem。如果列表中的元素是纯字符串，则Text值最好。现有实体最适合用于简单，无序地列出数据中的现有事物。当您要提供有关该列表中元素的其他上下文时，或者当同一项目可能位于不同列表中的不同位置时，ListItem与有序列表一起使用。注意：标记中元素的顺序不足以指示顺序或元素。在这种情况下，请将ListItem与'position'属性一起使用。
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements.  Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.

内容的主题。: 排序类型（例如，升序，降序，无序）。
Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

内容的主题。: 物品的当前位置。
Current location of the item.

内容的主题。: 提供（或要求）的项目。要约或需求的交易性质使用businessFunction进行记录，例如出售，租赁等。在此定义中明确列出了几种常见的预期类型，但也可以使用其他类型。使用第二种类型（例如产品或产品的子类型）可以阐明要约的性质。
An item being offered (or demanded). The transactional nature of the offer or demand is documented using businessFunction, e.g. sell, lease etc. While several common expected types are listed explicitly in this definition, others can be used. Using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.
Thing: AggregateOffer, CreativeWork, Event, MenuItem, Product, Service, Trip

内容的主题。: 正在审查/定级的项目。
The item that is being reviewed/rated.

内容的主题。: 正在运送的物品。
Item(s) being shipped.

内容的主题。: 组成行程的目的地（地点）。对于目的地顺序很重要的旅程，请使用ItemList指定该顺序（请参见示例）。
Destination(s) ( Place ) that make up a trip. For a trip where destination order is important use ItemList to specify that order (see examples).

内容的主题。: 与工作相关的福利说明。
Description of benefits associated with the job.

内容的主题。: 关于是否有可立即开始的头寸的指标。
An indicator as to whether a position is available for an immediate start.

内容的主题。: 与工作位置关联的（通常为单个）地理位置。
A (typically single) geographic location associated with the job position.

内容的主题。: 作业位置的说明（例如，远程办公作业的TELECOMMUTE）。
A description of the job location (e.g TELECOMMUTE for telecommute jobs).

内容的主题。: 成功完成该工作的申请人应开始工作的日期。选择将来的特定日期，或使用jobImmediateStart属性指示该职位将尽快填补。
The date on which a successful applicant for this job would be expected to start work. Choose a specific date in the future or use the jobImmediateStart property to indicate the position is to be filled as soon as possible.

内容的主题。: 该人的职位（例如，财务经理）。
The job title of the person (for example, Financial Manager).

内容的主题。: 表示法律管辖权，例如一些立法，或某些政府服务的所在地。
Indicates a legal jurisdiction, e.g. of some legislation, or where some government service is based.

内容的主题。: 用于描述此内容的关键字或标签。关键字列表中的多个条目通常以逗号分隔。
Keywords or tags used to describe this content. Multiple entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas.

内容的主题。: 已知损害的文本描述，包括已修复和未修复。
A textual description of known damages, both repaired and unrepaired.

内容的主题。: 最通用的双向社交/工作关系。
The most generic bi-directional social/work relation.

内容的主题。: 一个人的意思，而不是一个组织的典型意思，表示一个已知的主题-暗示可能的专业知识，但并不暗示该主题。我们在此不区分技能水平，也不将其与教育内容，事件，目标或JobPosting描述相关。
Of a Person, and less typically of an Organization, to indicate a topic that is known about - suggesting possible expertise but not implying it. We do not distinguish skill levels here, or relate this to educational content, events, objectives or JobPosting descriptions.

内容的主题。: 表示一种已知语言的人，较不常见的是组织的语言。在此，我们不区分技能水平或阅读/写作/口语/签字。使用IETF BCP 47标准中的语言代码。
Of a Person, and less typically of an Organization, to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard.

内容的主题。: 链接到药物的标签详细信息。
Link to the drug's label details.

内容的主题。: 参与者的子属性。房地产所有者。
A sub property of participant. The owner of the real estate property.

内容的主题。: 仪器的子属性。此操作使用的语言。
A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.

内容的主题。: 上次检查本网页上内容的准确性和/或完整性的日期。
Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.

内容的主题。: 位置的纬度。例如37.42242（WGS 84）。
The latitude of a location. For example 37.42242 (WGS 84).

内容的主题。: 表征学习资源的主要类型或种类。例如，“演示”，“讲义”。
The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

内容的主题。: 某些住宿的租约期限，特定于某些要约或在某些情况下是该物业固有的。
Length of the lease for some Accommodation, either particular to some Offer or in some cases intrinsic to the property.

内容的主题。: 组织的正式名称，例如注册公司名称。
The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

内容的主题。: 药物或补品的法律地位，包括所有适用的受控物质时间表。
The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

内容的主题。: 表示该立法（或立法的一部分）以某种方式在不同的立法环境中转移了另一项立法。这是一个信息链接，没有法律价值。对于具有法律约束力的换位链接，请使用legalTransposes属性。例如，欧盟成员国的内容丰富的综合法“适用”其中实施的欧洲指令的综合版本。
Indicates that this legislation (or part of a legislation) somehow transfers another legislation in a different legislative context. This is an informative link, and it has no legal value. For legally-binding links of transposition, use the legislationTransposes property. For example an informative consolidated law of a European Union's member state "applies" the consolidated version of the European Directive implemented in it.

内容的主题。: 该立法改变的另一项立法。这包括修订，替换，更正，废除或其他类型的更改的概念。这可能是直接更改（文本或非文本修订），也可能是间接更改。该属性用于表示两个动作之间存在更改关系，而不是用于显示更改结果的文本的合并版本。对于合并关系，请使用legacyConsolidates属性。
Another legislation that this legislation changes. This encompasses the notions of amendment, replacement, correction, repeal, or other types of change. This may be a direct change (textual or non-textual amendment) or a consequential or indirect change. The property is to be used to express the existence of a change relationship between two acts rather than the existence of a consolidated version of the text that shows the result of the change. For consolidation relationships, use the legislationConsolidates property.

内容的主题。: 表示在此合并法规中考虑的另一项法规（通常是修改法规的编辑过程的产物）。应多次使用此属性，以同时引用原始版本或先前的合并版本以及进行更改的法规。
Indicates another legislation taken into account in this consolidated legislation (which is usually the product of an editorial process that revises the legislation). This property should be used multiple times to refer to both the original version or the previous consolidated version, and to the legislations making the change.

内容的主题。: 立法通过或签署的日期。这是该文本正式被承认为立法的日期，即使该文本甚至可能尚未发布或生效。
The date of adoption or signature of the legislation. This is the date at which the text is officially aknowledged to be a legislation, even though it might not even be published or in force.

内容的主题。: 所提供的法律描述有效的时间点（例如：在查看2016-04-07（= dateVersion）上的法律时，我得到了“国家《 2015年保险供款法》”）
The point-in-time at which the provided description of the legislation is valid (e.g. : when looking at the law on the 2016-04-07 (= dateVersion), I get the consolidation of 2015-04-12 of the "National Insurance Contributions Act 2015")

内容的主题。: 立法的标识符。它可以是基于字符串的标识符，例如欧盟级别的CELEX或法国的NOR，也可以是基于Web的URL / URI标识符，例如ELI（欧洲立法标识符）或URN-Lex。
An identifier for the legislation. This can be either a string-based identifier, like the CELEX at EU level or the NOR in France, or a web-based, URL/URI identifier, like an ELI (European Legislation Identifier) or an URN-Lex.

内容的主题。: 立法起源的司法管辖区。
The jurisdiction from which the legislation originates.

内容的主题。: 该立法是当前有效，无效或部分有效。
Whether the legislation is currently in force, not in force, or partially in force.

内容的主题。: 该立法文件的法律价值。相同的法规可以写入具有不同法律价值的多个文件中。通常，经过数字签名的PDF具有比同一行为的HTML文件“更强”的法律价值。
The legal value of this legislation file. The same legislation can be written in multiple files with different legal values. Typically a digitally signed PDF have a "stronger" legal value than the HTML file of the same act.

内容的主题。: 最初通过或制定法律的人或组织：通常是议会（对于主要立法）或政府（对于次要立法）。这表明法律的“合法作者”，而不是其自然作者。
The person or organization that originally passed or made the law : typically parliament (for primary legislation) or government (for secondary legislation). This indicates the "legal author" of the law, as opposed to its physical author.

内容的主题。: 对立法负有某种责任的个人或组织。通常情况下，负责制定法律的部门或负责该立法的潜在人员在法律发布后负责制定。
An individual or organization that has some kind of responsibility for the legislation. Typically the ministry who is/was in charge of elaborating the legislation, or the adressee for potential questions about the legislation once it is published.

内容的主题。: 表示该立法（或立法的一部分）通过采取适当的实施措施，实现了另一项立法设定的目标。通常，欧盟成员国或地区的某些法规会转而采用欧洲指令。这表明这两项法律之间具有法律约束力。
Indicates that this legislation (or part of legislation) fulfills the objectives set by another legislation, by passing appropriate implementation measures. Typically, some legislations of European Union's member states or regions transpose European Directives. This indicates a legally binding link between the 2 legislations.

内容的主题。: 立法的类型。值的示例取决于国家/地区，例如“法律”，“法案”，“指令”，“法令”，“法规”，“法定文书”，“组织意向书”，“大公r”等。
The type of the legislation. Examples of values are "law", "act", "directive", "decree", "regulation", "statutory instrument", "loi organique", "règlement grand-ducal", etc., depending on the country.

内容的主题。: 组织标识符，可唯一标识ISO 17442中定义的法人实体。
An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

内容的主题。: 参与者的子属性。借出对象的人。
A sub property of participant. The person that lends the object being borrowed.

内容的主题。: 定性值的这种排序关系表明主题比对象小。
This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

内容的主题。: 定性值的这种排序关系表明主题小于或等于对象。
This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

内容的主题。: 在艺术品上添加刻字（包括语音气球和声音效果）的个人。
The individual who adds lettering, including speech balloons and sound effects, to artwork.

内容的主题。: 适用于此内容的许可文档，通常由URL指示。
A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

内容的主题。: 一条线是由两个或多个点组成的点对点路径。一条线表示为一系列由空格隔开的两个或多个点对象。
A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

内容的主题。: 表示Web链接的关系类型。
Indicates the relationship type of a Web link.

内容的主题。: LiveBlog的更新。
An update to the LiveBlog.

内容的主题。: 可以在以后阶段转换为适当抵押的抵押授权额。
Amount of mortgage mandate that can be converted into a proper mortgage at a later stage.

内容的主题。: 一次付款要支付的金额。
The amount of money to pay in a single payment.

内容的主题。: 到期付款频率，即两次付款之间的月数。这被定义为频率，即一段时间的倒数。
Frequency of payments due, i.e. number of months between payments. This is defined as a frequency, i.e. the reciprocal of a period of time.

内容的主题。: 一种偿还先前从贷方借来的钱的形式。还款通常采取定期付款的形式，通常包括部分本金加上每次付款的利息。
A form of paying back money previously borrowed from a lender. Repayment usually takes the form of periodic payments that normally include part principal plus interest in each payment.

内容的主题。: 贷款或信贷协议的期限。
The duration of the loan or credit agreement.

内容的主题。: 贷款或信贷的类型。
The type of a loan or credit.

内容的主题。: 例如事件发生的位置，组织所在的位置或操作发生的位置。
The location of for example where the event is happening, an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

内容的主题。: 创建CreativeWork的位置，该位置可能与CreativeWork中描述的位置不同。
The location where the CreativeWork was created, which may not be the same as the location depicted in the CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 住宿单位的完整说明。
A full description of the lodging unit.

内容的主题。: 单位类型的文字说明（包括套房与房间，床的大小等）。
Textual description of the unit type (including suite vs. room, size of bed, etc.).

内容的主题。: 关联的徽标。
An associated logo.
The longitude of a location. For example -122.08585 (WGS 84).

内容的主题。: 参与者的子属性。行动的失败者。
A sub property of participant. The loser of the action.

内容的主题。: 所有报价中的最低价格使用指南：使用值从0123456789（Unicode“数字零”（U + 0030）到“数字九”（U + 0039）），而不是表面上类似的Unicode符号。 （Unicode'FULL STOP'（U + 002E））而不是'，'表示小数点。避免将这些符号用作可读性分隔符。
The lowest price of all offers available.Usage guidelines:Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

内容的主题。: 写词的人。
The person who wrote the words.

内容的主题。: 歌曲中的词。
The words in the song.

内容的主题。: 指示此网页元素是否是页面的主要主题。
Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.

内容的主题。: 指示某个页面或其他CreativeWork中描述的主要实体。
Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 指示此内容是所描述的主要实体的页面（或其他CreativeWork）。有关详细信息，请参见背景说明。
Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main entity being described. See background notes for details.

内容的主题。: 数据集，软件包（SoftwareApplication）或其他项目的维护者。维护者是管理某些（通常是复杂的）工件的贡献和/或发布的人员或组织。软件和数据的分发通常基于“上游”源。当维护者应用于某事物的特定版本时，例如特定的版本或数据集的包装，上游源总是有不同的维护者。 isBasedOn属性可用于指示数据集之间的此类关系，以使不同的维护角色清晰明了。类似地，就软件而言，程序包可能具有专门的维护人员，他们致力于集成到软件发行版（如Ubuntu）中，以及基础工作的上游维护人员。
A maintainer of a Dataset, software package (SoftwareApplication), or other Project. A maintainer is a Person or Organization that manages contributions to, and/or publication of, some (typically complex) artifact. It is common for distributions of software and data to be based on "upstream" sources. When maintainer is applied to a specific version of something e.g. a particular version or packaging of a Dataset, it is always  possible that the upstream source has a different maintainer. The isBasedOn property can be used to indicate such relationships between datasets to make the different maintenance roles clear. Similarly in the case of software, a package may have dedicated maintainers working on integration into software distributions such as Ubuntu, as well as upstream maintainers of the underlying work.

内容的主题。: 指向组织或个人提供的产品或服务的指针。
A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

内容的主题。: 产品的制造商。
The manufacturer of the product.

内容的主题。: 地点地图的网址。
A URL to a map of the place.

内容的主题。: 从MapCategoryType枚举中指示地图的类型。
Indicates the kind of Map, from the MapCategoryType Enumeration.

内容的主题。: 地点地图的网址。
A URL to a map of the place.

内容的主题。: 用于观察的marginOfError。
A marginOfError for an Observation.

内容的主题。: 对于NewsMediaOrganization，是指向标头页面或列出顶级编辑管理页面的链接。
For a NewsMediaOrganization, a link to the masthead page or a page listing top editorial management.

内容的主题。: 一种由某物制成的材料，例如 皮革，羊毛，棉，纸。
A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

内容的主题。: 被描述的材料的数量或它们所占据的物理空间的表达。
The quantity of the materials being described or an expression of the physical space they occupy.

内容的主题。: 价格是范围内的最高价格。
The highest price if the price is a range.

内容的主题。: 某些特征或特性的上限值。
The upper value of some characteristic or property.

内容的主题。: 可以参加活动或地点的个人总数。
The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.

内容的主题。: 可以注册该计划的最大学生人数。
The maximum number of students who may be enrolled in the program.

内容的主题。: 根据特定推荐机构的定义，针对特定人群的这种补充剂的推荐摄入量。
Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

内容的主题。: 事件eventAttendanceMode为OfflineEventAttendanceMode（或在MixedEventAttendanceMode情况下为脱机方面）的事件的最大物理出席者容量。
The maximum physical attendee capacity of an Event whose eventAttendanceMode is OfflineEventAttendanceMode (or the offline aspects, in the case of a MixedEventAttendanceMode).

内容的主题。: EventAttendanceMode为OnlineEventAttendanceMode（或在线方面，如果为MixedEventAttendanceMode）的事件的最大物理出席者容量。
The maximum physical attendee capacity of an Event whose eventAttendanceMode is OnlineEventAttendanceMode (or the online aspects, in the case of a MixedEventAttendanceMode).

内容的主题。: 将提供或可供购买的餐食的说明。
Description of the meals that will be provided or available for purchase.

内容的主题。: 观测值的measuredProperty，可以是schema.org属性，也可以是其他RDF兼容系统的属性，例如W3C RDF数据多维数据集或schema.org扩展，例如GS1。
The measuredProperty of an Observation, either a schema.org property, a property from other RDF-compatible systems e.g. W3C RDF Data Cube, or schema.org extensions such as GS1's.

内容的主题。: 观测值的实测值。
The measuredValue of an Observation.

内容的主题。: 数据集（或数据下载，数据目录）中使用的一种或多种技术，与用于测量相应变量的方法相对应（使用variableMeasured描述）。这是面向科学和学术数据集的发布，但可能具有更广泛的适用性。例如，如果variableMeasured为：分子浓度，测量技术，则可能为：“质谱”或“ nmr光谱”或“比色法”或“ “免疫荧光”。如果变量Measured是“抑郁等级”，则测量技术可以是“ Zung Scale”或“ HAM-D”或“贝克抑郁清单”。如果为某些给定数据对象记录了多个variableMeasured属性，请使用PropertyValue为每个变量测量并附加相应的测量技术。
A technique or technology used in a Dataset (or DataDownload, DataCatalog),corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (described using variableMeasured). This is oriented towards scientific and scholarly dataset publication but may have broader applicability; it is not intended as a full representation of measurement, but rather as a high level summary for dataset discovery.For example, if variableMeasured is: molecule concentration, measurementTechnique could be: "mass spectrometry" or "nmr spectroscopy" or "colorimetry" or "immunofluorescence".If the variableMeasured is "depression rating", the measurementTechnique could be "Zung Scale" or "HAM-D" or "Beck Depression Inventory".If there are several variableMeasured properties recorded for some given data object, use a PropertyValue for each variableMeasured and attach the corresponding measurementTechnique.

内容的主题。: 药物或补品通过其产生药理作用的特定生化相互作用。
The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

内容的主题。: 指示媒体对象的MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration分类（在如何发布或共享的上下文中）。
Indicates a MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration classification of a media object (in the context of how it was published or shared).

内容的主题。: 中值。
The median value.

内容的主题。: 提供者的医学专业。
A medical specialty of the provider.

内容的主题。: 包含此MedicalEntity的医学系统，例如“循证医学”，“顺势疗法”，“整脊疗法”等。
The system of medicine that includes this MedicalEntity, for example 'evidence-based', 'homeopathic', 'chiropractic', etc.

内容的主题。: 表示车辆符合相应的排放标准。
Indicates that the vehicle meets the respective emission standard.

内容的主题。: 组织或计划成员的成员。组织可以是组织的成员； ProgramMembership通常是针对个人的。
A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

内容的主题。: 该人员或组织所属的组织（或ProgramMembership）。
An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

内容的主题。: 该组织的成员。
A member of this organization.

内容的主题。: 成员身份的唯一标识符。
A unique identifier for the membership.

内容的主题。: 会员获得的会员积分数。如有必要，可以使用unitText来表示发出积分的单位（例如星号，英里等）。
The number of membership points earned by the member. If necessary, the unitText can be used to express the units the points are issued in. (e.g. stars, miles, etc.)

内容的主题。: 最低内存要求。
Minimum memory requirements.

内容的主题。: 表示CreativeWork包含对概念的引用，但不一定涉及概念。
Indicates that the CreativeWork contains a reference to, but is not necessarily about a concept.

内容的主题。: 实际菜单可以是结构化表示形式，文本形式，也可以是菜单的URL。
Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

内容的主题。: 可以添加到此菜单项的其他菜单项，例如沙拉配菜或薯条配菜。此外，它可以是一个菜单部分，其中包含该菜单项允许的附加菜单项。
Additional menu item(s) such as a side dish of salad or side order of fries that can be added to this menu item. Additionally it can be a menu section containing allowed add-on menu items for this menu item.

内容的主题。: “商人”是“卖方”的过时术语。
'merchant' is an out-dated term for 'seller'.

内容的主题。: vendorReturnDays属性指示相关商人退货政策适用的天数（自购买起）。
The merchantReturnDays property indicates the number of days (from purchase) within which relevant merchant return policy is applicable.

内容的主题。: 通过URL指示网页或服务，以返回产品。
Indicates a Web page or service by URL, for product return.

内容的主题。: 邮件附带的CreativeWork。
A CreativeWork attached to the message.

内容的主题。: 从里程表中读取的特定车辆自首次生产以来的总行驶距离。典型单位代码：KMT（公里），SMI（法定英里）
The total distance travelled by the particular vehicle since its initial production, as read from its odometer.Typical unit code(s): KMT for kilometers, SMI for statute miles

内容的主题。: 如果价格是范围内的最低价格。
The lowest price if the price is a range.

内容的主题。: 某些特性或属性的较低值。
The lower value of some characteristic or property.

内容的主题。: 目前所需的最低付款额。
The minimum payment required at this time.

内容的主题。: 对于NewsMediaOrganization，是关于报道优先级的声明，包括有关问题的任何公共议程或立场。
For a NewsMediaOrganization, a statement on coverage priorities, including any public agenda or stance on issues.

内容的主题。: 产品的型号。与ProductModel的URL或模型标识符的文本表示一起使用。 ProductModel的URL可以来自外部来源。建议通过gtin8 / gtin13 / gtin14和mpn属性另外提供强大的产品标识符。
The model of the product. Use with the URL of a ProductModel or a textual representation of the model identifier. The URL of the ProductModel can be from an external source. It is recommended to additionally provide strong product identifiers via the gtin8/gtin13/gtin14 and mpn properties.

内容的主题。: 车辆模型的发布日期（通常用于区分同一品牌和型号的版本）。
The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

内容的主题。: 修改保留的日期和时间。
The date and time the reservation was modified.

内容的主题。: 最低付款额是每月需要在信用卡对帐单上支付的最低金额。
The minimum payment is the lowest amount of money that one is required to pay on a credit card statement each month.

内容的主题。: 产品或报价所指产品的制造商零件编号（MPN）。
The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

内容的主题。: 该属性是否允许多个值。默认为false。
Whether multiple values are allowed for the property.  Default is false.

内容的主题。: 肌肉产生的运动。
The movement the muscle generates.

内容的主题。: 从构图派生的安排。
An arrangement derived from the composition.

内容的主题。: 配乐的作曲家。
The composer of the soundtrack.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: Clip, Episode, Movie, MovieSeries, RadioSeries, TVSeries, VideoGame, VideoGameSeries, VideoObject

内容的主题。: 作品的类型（例如序曲，奏鸣曲，交响曲等）。
The type of composition (e.g. overture, sonata, symphony, etc.).

内容的主题。: 音乐小组的成员：例如John，Paul，George或Ringo。
A member of a music group: for example, John, Paul, George, or Ringo.

内容的主题。: 此发行版的格式（使用的记录媒体的类型，即光盘，数字媒体，LP等）。
Format of this release (the type of recording media used, ie. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

内容的主题。: 此合成使用的键，模式或缩放。
The key, mode, or scale this composition uses.

内容的主题。: 特定组织或业务人员的北美行业分类系统（NAICS）代码。
The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

内容的主题。: 项目的名称。
The name of the item.

内容的主题。: 个人或组织作为组织一部分所扮演，执行或填补的职位。例如，SportsTeam中的运动员可能在名为“ Quarterback”的位置上比赛。
A position played, performed or filled by a person or organization, as part of an organization. For example, an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

内容的主题。: 该人的国籍。
Nationality of the person.

内容的主题。: 如果不进行治疗并使其自然进展，则疾病的预期进展。
The expected progression of the condition if it is not treated and allowed to progress naturally.

内容的主题。: 与肌肉相关的潜在神经支配。
The underlying innervation associated with the muscle.

内容的主题。: 涉及肌肉控制的神经系统途径延伸。
The neurological pathway extension that involves muscle control.

内容的主题。: 通过从负债中减去资产计算得出的人的总财务价值。
The total financial value of the person as calculated by subtracting assets from liabilities.

内容的主题。: 指示包含新闻更新和准则的页面。这通常可能是（但不是必须如此）网站上包含SpecialAnnouncement标记的主页。
Indicates a page with news updates and guidelines. This could often be (but is not required to be) the main page containing SpecialAnnouncement markup on a site.

内容的主题。: 指向当前项之后的ListItem的链接。
A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

内容的主题。: 对于NewsMediaOrganization或其他与新闻相关的组织，该声明说明何时未在标题行中命名文章作者。
For a NewsMediaOrganization or other news-related Organization, a statement explaining when authors of articles are not named in bylines.

内容的主题。: 定性值的这种排序关系表明主题不等于对象。
This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is not equal to the object.

内容的主题。: 该药物或补品的通用名称。
The generic name of this drug or supplement.

内容的主题。: 非营利状态表示非营利组织在其主要营业地点的法律地位。
nonprofit Status indicates the legal status of a non-profit organization in its primary place of business.

内容的主题。: 如果适用，典型患者的可接受值范围。
Range of acceptable values for a typical patient, when applicable.

内容的主题。: 表示产品的北约库存号（nsn）。
Indicates the NATO stock number (nsn) of a Product.

内容的主题。: 住在该单位的成人人数。
The number of adults staying in the unit.

内容的主题。: 留在该单位的儿童人数。
The number of children staying in the unit.

内容的主题。: 指示为特定的StatisticalPopulation定义的约束数量（不计算种群类型）。这可以帮助应用程序了解他们是否可以访问StatisticalPopulation的足够完整的描述。
Indicates the number of constraints (not counting populationType) defined for a particular StatisticalPopulation. This helps applications understand if they have access to a sufficiently complete description of a StatisticalPopulation.

内容的主题。: 此专辑或播放列表中的曲目数。
The number of tracks in this album or playlist.

内容的主题。: 指示ApartmentComplex中住宿单元的总数（可用加不可用），或特定FloorPlan（在其特定ApartmentComplex中）的住宿单元数。另请参见numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits。
Indicates the total (available plus unavailable) number of accommodation units in an ApartmentComplex, or the number of accommodation units for a specific FloorPlan (within its specific ApartmentComplex). See also numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits.

内容的主题。: 车辆中安全气囊的数量或类型。
The number or type of airbags in the vehicle.

内容的主题。: 指示ApartmentComplex中可用住宿单位的数量，或特定FloorPlan（在其特定ApartmentComplex中）的住宿单位的数量。另请参见numberOfAccommodationUnits。
Indicates the number of available accommodation units in an ApartmentComplex, or the number of accommodation units for a specific FloorPlan (within its specific ApartmentComplex). See also numberOfAccommodationUnits.

内容的主题。: 轴数典型单位代码C62
The number of axles.Typical unit code(s): C62

内容的主题。: 根据RESO中记录的房地产惯例，某些住宿中浴室的总数为整数：“浴室数量的简单总和。例如，对于具有两个完整浴室和一个半浴室的物业，浴室总数将为3.”。另请参见numberOfRooms。
The total integer number of bathrooms in a some Accommodation, following real estate conventions as documented in RESO: "The simple sum of the number of bathrooms. For example for a property with two Full Bathrooms and one Half Bathroom, the Bathrooms Total Integer will be 3.". See also numberOfRooms.

内容的主题。: 某些Accommodation，ApartmentComplex或FloorPlan中卧室总数的整数。
The total integer number of bedrooms in a some Accommodation, ApartmentComplex or FloorPlan.

内容的主题。: HotelRoom，Suite，House或Apartment中可用的指定床型数量。
The quantity of the given bed type available in the HotelRoom, Suite, House, or Apartment.

内容的主题。: 课程授予或完成“教育职业计划”所需的学分或学分数量。
The number of credits or units awarded by a Course or required to complete an EducationalOccupationalProgram.

内容的主题。: 门数量典型单位代码C62
The number of doors.Typical unit code(s): C62

内容的主题。: 组织中的员工人数，例如商业。
The number of employees in an organization e.g. business.

内容的主题。: 本季或系列中的剧集数。
The number of episodes in this season or series.

内容的主题。: 可用于车辆传动系统的前进挡总数。典型单位代码：C62
The total number of forward gears available for the transmission system of the vehicle.Typical unit code(s): C62

内容的主题。: 完整浴室数量-住宿中完整浴室和¾浴室的总数。这对应于RESO中的BathroomsFull字段。
Number of full bathrooms - The total number of full and ¾ bathrooms in an Accommodation. This corresponds to the BathroomsFull field in RESO.

内容的主题。: ItemList中的项目数。请注意，某些描述可能无法完全描述列表中的所有项目（例如，多页分页）；在这种情况下，numberOfItems将用于整个列表。
The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

内容的主题。: 发起时按合同要求偿还贷款的次数。对于按月还款的贷款，这是从合同首次还款日期到到期日期的月数。
The number of payments contractually required at origination to repay the loan. For monthly paying loans this is the number of months from the contractual first payment date to the maturity date.

内容的主题。: 书中的页数。
The number of pages in the book.

内容的主题。: 部分浴室的数量-住宿中半浴室和¼浴室的总数。这对应于RESO中的BathroomsPartial字段。
Number of partial bathrooms - The total number of half and ¼ bathrooms in an Accommodation. This corresponds to the BathroomsPartial field in RESO.

内容的主题。: 指出可以玩多少人（最小，最大或范围）。
Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

内容的主题。: 车辆拥有者的数量，包括当前的拥有者。典型单位代码：C62
The number of owners of the vehicle, including the current one.Typical unit code(s): C62

内容的主题。: 住宿或住宿业务的房间数（不包括浴室和壁橱）。典型的单位代码：ROM用于房间，C62用于无房间。房间的类型可以放在QuantitativeValue的unitText属性中。
The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business.Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: Accommodation, Apartment, FloorPlan, House, LodgingBusiness, SingleFamilyResidence, Suite

内容的主题。: 该系列的季节数。
The number of seasons in this series.

内容的主题。: 与组织中的角色相关的数字，例如运动员球衣上的数字。
A number associated with a role in an organization, for example, the number on an athlete's jersey.

内容的主题。: 有关食谱或菜单项的营养信息。
Nutrition information about the recipe or menu item.

内容的主题。: 对其执行操作的对象，其状态保持不变或已更改。也称为患者，受影响者或经历者（更改其状态）或主题（不更改）的语义角色。例如约翰读了一本书。
The object upon which the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). e.g. John read a book.

内容的主题。: 观察的观察日期。
The observationDate of an Observation.

内容的主题。: 观察值的被观察节点，通常是统计人口。
The observedNode of an Observation, often a StatisticalPopulation.

内容的主题。: 可容纳的总人数（包括婴儿等）。对于个人住宿，这不一定是法定最高限额，而是根据合同协议定义允许的使用范围（例如，单人使用的双人间）典型单位代码：C62
The allowed total occupancy for the accommodation in persons (including infants etc). For individual accommodations, this is not necessarily the legal maximum but defines the permitted usage as per the contractual agreement (e.g. a double room used by a single person).Typical unit code(s): C62 for person

内容的主题。: 此职业说明适合的地区/国家。请注意，不同地区的教育要求和资格可能有所不同。
The region/country for which this occupational description is appropriate. Note that educational requirements and qualifications can vary between jurisdictions.

内容的主题。: 描述工作的类别，最好使用分类法中的术语，例如BLS O * NET-SOC，ISCO-08或类似术语，并为每个适用的值重复属性。理想情况下，应识别分类法，并提供类别的文本标签和正式代码。注意：出于历史原因，可以假定以文字形式提供的任何文本标签和正式代码来自O * NET-SOC。
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as BLS O*NET-SOC, ISCO-08 or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed to be from O*NET-SOC.

内容的主题。: 成功完成本课程或课程后所获得的资格，奖励，证书，文凭或其他职业证书的说明。
A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other occupational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

内容的主题。: 产品的报价数量。
The number of offers for the product.

内容的主题。: 指向要约的组织或个人的指针。
A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

内容的主题。: 提供此项的要约：例如，要出售产品，租借电影DVD，执行服务或赠送活动门票的要约。 使用businessFunction指示提供的交易类型，即出售，租赁等。此属性还可用于描述需求。 虽然按预期在许多常见类型上列出了此属性，但可以在其他类型中使用它。 在这种情况下，使用第二种类型（例如产品或产品的子类型）可以阐明要约的性质。
An offer to provide this item: for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use businessFunction to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a Demand. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: AggregateOffer, CreativeWork, EducationalOccupationalProgram, Event, MenuItem, Product, Service, Trip

内容的主题。: 处方是否可以邮寄。
Whether prescriptions can be delivered by mail.

内容的主题。: 企业的一般营业时间。
The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00. Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

内容的主题。: 某个地方的营业时间。
The opening hours of a certain place.

内容的主题。: 一周中给定日期的地点或服务的开放时间。
The opening hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

内容的主题。: 支持的操作系统（Windows 7，OSX 10.6，Android 1.6）。
Operating systems supported (Windows 7, OSX 10.6, Android 1.6).

内容的主题。: 参与者的子属性。 对手在此行动。
A sub property of participant. The opponent on this action.

内容的主题。: 对象的子属性。 这些选项受此操作的影响。
A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

内容的主题。: 下订单的日期。
Date order was placed.

内容的主题。: 与该订单或订单项目相关的包裹的交付。
The delivery of the parcel related to this order or order item.

内容的主题。: 订单商品的标识符。
The identifier of the order item.

内容的主题。: 订单商品的当前状态。
The current status of the order item.

内容的主题。: 交易的标识符。
The identifier of the transaction.

内容的主题。: 订购的商品编号。 如果未设置该属性，则假定数量为1。
The number of the item ordered. If the property is not set, assume the quantity is one.

内容的主题。: 订单的当前状态。
The current status of the order.

内容的主题。: 该商品已订购。
The item ordered.

内容的主题。: 活动的组织者。
An organizer of an Event.

内容的主题。: 托运人的地址。
Shipper's address.

内容的主题。: 淋巴结构的脉管系统起源或传入。
The vasculature the lymphatic structure originates, or afferents, from.

内容的主题。: 与药物过量相关的任何信息，包括体征或症状，治疗，紧急响应的联系信息。
Any information related to overdose on a drug, including signs or symptoms, treatments, contact information for emergency response.

内容的主题。: 获得产品的日期和时间。
The date and time of obtaining the product.

内容的主题。: 放弃产品所有权的日期和时间。
The date and time of giving up ownership on the product.

内容的主题。: 对于组织（通常但不一定是NewsMediaOrganization），描述组织所有权结构；资金和赠款。在新闻/媒体环境中，这特别涉及编辑独立性。请注意，也可以使用出纳者，并且可以使用该出纳者使基本出纳者信息机器可读。
For an Organization (often but not necessarily a NewsMediaOrganization), a description of organizational ownership structure; funding and grants. In a news/media setting, this is with particular reference to editorial independence.   Note that the funder is also available and can be used to make basic funder information machine-readable.

内容的主题。: 组织或个人拥有的产品。
Products owned by the organization or person.

内容的主题。: 工作结束的页面；例如“ 138”或“ xvi”。
The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

内容的主题。: 工作开始的页面；例如“ 135”或“ xiii”。
The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

内容的主题。: 没有分为pageStart和pageEnd的页面的任何描述；例如“ 1-6、9、55”或“ 10-12、46-49”。
Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

内容的主题。: 此人的父母。
A parent of this person.

内容的主题。: 一般是问题，答案或项目的父项。
The parent of a question, answer or item in general.

内容的主题。: 该组织是子组织的较大组织（如果有）。
The larger organization that this organization is a subOrganization of, if any.

内容的主题。: 广播服务所属的广播服务，例如国家频道的区域变化。
A broadcast service to which the broadcast service may belong to such as regional variations of a national channel.

内容的主题。: 该人的父母。
A parents of the person.

内容的主题。: 该剪辑所属的剧集。
The episode to which this clip belongs.

内容的主题。: 订单将作为参考发票的一部分支付。
The order is being paid as part of the referenced Invoice.

内容的主题。: 包括此交货中物料的总体订单。
The overall order the items in this delivery were included in.

内容的主题。: 此剧集所属的季节。
The season to which this episode belongs.

内容的主题。: 此剧集或本季所属的系列。
The series to which this episode or season belongs.

内容的主题。: 该结构所在的解剖或器官系统。
The anatomical or organ system that this structure is part of.

内容的主题。: 此剧集或本季所属的电视连续剧。
The TV series to which this episode or season belongs.

内容的主题。: 标识此行程是另一个行程的子行程。 例如，多日行程的第1天，第2天等。
Identifies that this Trip is a subTrip of another Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

内容的主题。: 其他间接参与行动的共同代理人。 例如 约翰与史蒂夫（Steve）写了一本书。
Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. e.g. John wrote a book with Steve.

内容的主题。: 预订应容纳的人数。
Number of people the reservation should accommodate.

内容的主题。: 为安全或登机而分配给乘客的优先级状态（例如FastTrack或Priority）。
The priority status assigned to a passenger for security or boarding (e.g. FastTrack or Priority).

内容的主题。: 航空公司分配的乘客的序列号。
The passenger's sequence number as assigned by the airline.

内容的主题。: 与此活动或状况相关的正常机械，物理和生化功能的变化。
Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

内容的主题。: 乘客和货物的允许重量（不包括空车的重量）典型单位代码：KGM表示千克，LBR表示注意1：许多数据库改为指定允许的总重量，即重量和有效载荷之和注2 ：您可以在QuantitativeValue节点的名称中指示其他信息。注3：您也可以使用valueReference链接到提供附加信息的QualitativeValue节点。注4：请注意，可以使用minValue和maxValue指示范围。
The permitted weight of passengers and cargo, EXCLUDING the weight of the empty vehicle.Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for poundNote 1: Many databases specify the permitted TOTAL weight instead, which is the sum of weight and payloadNote 2: You can indicate additional information in the name of the QuantitativeValue node.Note 3: You may also link to a QualitativeValue node that provides additional information using valueReference.Note 4: Note that you can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.

内容的主题。: 现金，信用卡，加密货币，本地交易所交易系统等
Cash, Credit Card, Cryptocurrency, Local Exchange Tradings System, etc.

内容的主题。: 付款到期日。
The date that payment is due.

内容的主题。: 付款到期日。
The date that payment is due.

内容的主题。: 订单的信用卡名称或其他付款方式。
The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

内容的主题。: 所用付款方式的标识符（例如信用卡的后4位）。
An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

内容的主题。: 付款状态；发票是否已付款。
The status of payment; whether the invoice has been paid or not.

内容的主题。: 用于发送付款的网址。
The URL for sending a payment.

内容的主题。: 绘制主要叙事作品的个人。
The individual who draws the primary narrative artwork.

内容的主题。: 第十个百分点值。
The 10th percentile value.

内容的主题。: 第25个百分点值。
The 25th percentile value.

内容的主题。: 第75个百分位值。
The 75th percentile value.

内容的主题。: 第90个百分位值。
The 90th percentile value.

内容的主题。: 以ISO 8601持续时间格式执行指令或指示所花费的时间长度（不包括准备耗材的时间）。
The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in ISO 8601 duration format.

内容的主题。: 活动中的表演者：例如，主持人，音乐家，音乐团体或演员。
A performer at the event: for example, a presenter, musician, musical group or actor.

内容的主题。: 此人是表演者或参与者的事件。
Event that this person is a performer or participant in.

内容的主题。: 活动的主要执行者：例如，主持人，音乐家或演员。
The main performer or performers of the event: for example, a presenter, musician, or actor.

内容的主题。: 授予个人，组织或受众的许可类型。
The type of permission granted the person, organization, or audience.

内容的主题。: 运行该应用所需的权限（例如，移动应用可能需要完全的Internet访问权限，或者只能在wifi上运行）。
Permission(s) required to run the app (for example, a mobile app may require full internet access or may run only on wifi).

内容的主题。: 此许可证的目标受众。
The target audience for this permit.

内容的主题。: 关于住宿的允许使用的指示。
Indications regarding the permitted usage of the accommodation.

内容的主题。: 指示是否允许宠物进入住宿或住宿业务。 更详细的信息可以放在文本值中。
Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.

内容的主题。: 使用指定的SpeechToTextMarkup表示文本textValue。 例如，IPA中休斯顿的城市名称：/ ˈhjuːstən /。
Representation of a text textValue using the specified speechToTextMarkup. For example the city name of Houston in IPA: /ˈhjuːstən/.

内容的主题。: 这个地方的照片。
A photograph of this place.

内容的主题。: 这个地方的照片。
Photographs of this place.

内容的主题。: 与工作相关的体育活动类型的描述。 可以使用诸如O * net中的已定义术语，但是请注意，使用已定义术语时，无法指定能力级别及其性质。
A description of the types of physical activity associated with the job. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

内容的主题。: 与计划相关的特定生理益处。
Specific physiologic benefits associated to the plan.

内容的主题。: 出租车可以接载乘客或租车的地方。
Where a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

内容的主题。: 出租车可接载乘客或出租汽车时，可将其接载。
When a taxi will pickup a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

内容的主题。: 指示该游戏是多人游戏，合作游戏还是单人游戏。可以同时将游戏标记为多人游戏，合作游戏和单人游戏。
Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.  The game can be marked as multi-player, co-op and single-player at the same time.

内容的主题。: 所需的播放器类型：例如Flash或Silverlight。
Player type required: for example, Flash or Silverlight.

内容的主题。: 服务器上的播放器数量。
Number of players on the server.

内容的主题。: 多边形是由点到点路径包围的区域，起点和终点相同。多边形表示为一系列四个或更多空间分隔点，其中第一个点和最后一个点相同。
A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.

内容的主题。: 指示统计人口的所有成员共有的人口类型。
Indicates the populationType common to all members of a StatisticalPopulation.

内容的主题。: 项目在一系列或一系列项目中的位置。
The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

内容的主题。: 医疗状况可能发生的意外和不利变化。并发症可能包括疾病的体征或症状恶化，病情扩展至其他器官系统等。
A possible unexpected and unfavorable evolution of a medical condition. Complications may include worsening of the signs or symptoms of the disease, extension of the condition to other organ systems, etc.

内容的主题。: 解决这种情况，体征或症状的可能方法。
A possible treatment to address this condition, sign or symptom.

内容的主题。: 邮政信箱地址的邮政信箱号码。
The post office box number for PO box addresses.

内容的主题。: 该设备的术后程序，护理和/或随访说明。
A description of the postoperative procedures, care, and/or followups for this device.

内容的主题。: 邮政编码。 例如94043。
The postal code. For example, 94043.

内容的主题。: 范围内的第一个邮政编码（包括在内）。
First postal code in a range (included).

内容的主题。: 范围内的最后一个邮政编码（包括在内）。 需要在postalCodeBegin之后。
Last postal code in the range (included). Needs to be after postalCodeBegin.

内容的主题。: 由共同的文本前缀指示的邮政编码的定义范围。 用于非数字系统，例如UK。
A defined range of postal codes indicated by a common textual prefix. Used for non-numeric systems such as UK.

内容的主题。: 定义的邮政编码范围。
A defined range of postal codes.

内容的主题。: 表示潜在的动作，它描述了一种理想的动作，该动作将在其中扮演“对象”角色。
Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which this thing would play an 'object' role.

内容的主题。: 植入此设备之前需要进行的工作，测试和其他准备工作的说明。
A description of the workup, testing, and other preparations required before implanting this device.

内容的主题。: 从产品的先前（通常是已停产）变体到其新变体的指针。
A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

内容的主题。: 该药物的怀孕类别。
Pregnancy category of this drug.

内容的主题。: 与该药物在怀孕期间的使用有关的任何预防措施，指南，禁忌症等。
Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use during pregnancy.

内容的主题。: 以ISO 8601持续时间格式准备要在指令或指示中使用的项目所花费的时间长度。
The length of time it takes to prepare the items to be used in instructions or a direction, in ISO 8601 duration format.

内容的主题。: 患者在执行该程序之前必须进行的典型准备工作。
Typical preparation that a patient must undergo before having the procedure performed.

内容的主题。: 链接到该药的处方信息。
Link to prescribing information for the drug.

内容的主题。: 指示药物处方的状态，例如本地目录分类或是否可以通过处方药或非处方药等获得该药物。
Indicates the status of drug prescription eg. local catalogs classifications or whether the drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter, etc.

内容的主题。: 指向当前项之前的ListItem的链接。
A link to the ListItem that preceeds the current one.

内容的主题。: 与eventStatus一起用于重新安排或取消的事件。此属性包含先前安排的开始日期。对于重新安排的事件，应将startDate属性用于新安排的开始日期。在事件已经（多次）被推迟和重新安排多次的情况下，可以重复此字段。
Used in conjunction with eventStatus for rescheduled or cancelled events. This property contains the previously scheduled start date. For rescheduled events, the startDate property should be used for the newly scheduled start date. In the (rare) case of an event that has been postponed and rescheduled multiple times, this field may be repeated.

内容的主题。: 使用准则：使用priceCurrency属性（标准格式：ISO 4217货币格式，例如“ USD”；加密货币的交易代码，例如“ BTC”；使用价格货币属性）。本地交易系统（LETS）和其他货币类型的知名名称，例如“ Ithaca HOUR”），而不是在值中包含模糊的符号（例如“ $”）。用 '。' （Unicode'FULL STOP'（U + 002E））而不是'，'表示小数点。避免将这些符号用作可读性分隔符。请注意，RDFa和Microdata语法均允许使用“ content =”属性来发布简单的机器可读值以及更人性化的格式。请使用0123456789（Unicode'DIGIT ZERO'（U + 0030）至'DIGIT NINE'）中的值（（U + 0039）），而不是表面上类似的Unicode符号。
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.Usage guidelines:Use the priceCurrency property (with standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including ambiguous symbols such as '$' in the value. Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator. Note that both RDFa and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.

内容的主题。: 此属性链接到所有并行应用于CompoundPriceSpecification节点的UnitPriceSpecification节点。
This property links to all UnitPriceSpecification nodes that apply in parallel for the CompoundPriceSpecification node.

内容的主题。: 价格的货币，或附加在PriceSpecification及其子类型上的价格成分。使用标准格式：ISO 4217货币格式，例如“美元”;加密货币的股票代码“ BTC”；本地交易系统（LETS）和其他货币类型的知名名称“ Ithaca HOUR”。
The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.Use standard formats: ISO 4217 currency format e.g. "USD"; Ticker symbol for cryptocurrencies e.g. "BTC"; well known names for Local Exchange Tradings Systems (LETS) and other currency types e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

内容的主题。: 商家的价格范围。
The price range of the business, for example $$$.

内容的主题。: 一个或多个详细的价格规格，指示单价以及交货或付款费用。
One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

内容的主题。: 简短文字或首字母缩写词，表示同一报价的多个价格规格，例如建议零售价为SRP，发票价格为INVOICE，主要用于汽车行业。
A short text or acronym indicating multiple price specifications for the same offer, e.g. SRP for the suggested retail price or INVOICE for the invoice price, mostly used in the car industry.

内容的主题。: 价格不再可用的日期。
The date after which the price is no longer available.

内容的主题。: 指示页面上的主图像。
Indicates the main image on the page.

内容的主题。: 一种预防性疗法，用于预防诸如疫苗接种之类的疾病的最初发生。
A preventative therapy used to prevent an initial occurrence of the medical condition, such as vaccination.

内容的主题。: 新闻文章在印刷版中出现的列号。
The number of the column in which the NewsArticle appears in the print edition.

内容的主题。: NewsArticle出现的印刷产品的版本。
The edition of the print product in which the NewsArticle appears.

内容的主题。: 如果此NewsArticle以印刷形式出现，则此字段表示在其上找到该文章的页面的名称。请注意，此字段用于确切的页面名称（例如A5，B18）。
If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the name of the page on which the article is found. Please note that this field is intended for the exact page name (e.g. A5, B18).

内容的主题。: 如果此NewsArticle出现在印刷品中，则此字段指示文章出现在的印刷品部分。
If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the print section in which the article appeared.

内容的主题。: 有关设置，使用和/或安装设备的过程的说明。
A description of the procedure involved in setting up, using, and/or installing the device.

内容的主题。: 手术类型，例如外科手术，无创手术或经皮手术。
The type of procedure, for example Surgical, Noninvasive, or Percutaneous.

内容的主题。: 使用此通道的服务的估计处理时间。
Estimated processing time for the service using this channel.

内容的主题。: 运行该应用程序所需的处理器体系结构（例如IA64）。
Processor architecture required to run the application (e.g. IA64).

内容的主题。: 制作作品的个人或组织（例如音乐专辑，电影，电视/广播系列等）。
The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, tv/radio series etc.).

内容的主题。: 服务产生的有形事物，例如护照，许可证等
The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

内容的主题。: 产品标识符，例如ISBN。例如：meta itemprop =“ productID” content =“ isbn：123-456-789”。
The product identifier, such as ISBN. For example: meta itemprop="productID" content="isbn:123-456-789".

内容的主题。: productReturnDays属性指示相关产品退货政策适用的天数（自购买起）。
The productReturnDays property indicates the number of days (from purchase) within which relevant product return policy is applicable.

内容的主题。: 通过URL指示网页或服务，以返回产品。
Indicates a Web page or service by URL, for product return.

内容的主题。: 该支持联系点与之相关的产品或服务（例如特定产品系列的产品支持）。这可以是特定的产品或产品系列（例如“ iPhone”），也可以是产品或服务的一般类别（例如“智能手机”）。
The product or service this support contact point is related to (such as product support for a particular product line). This can be a specific product or product line (e.g. "iPhone") or a general category of products or services (e.g. "smartphones").

内容的主题。: 负责该项目的制作公司或工作室，例如系列，视频游戏，剧集等
The production company or studio responsible for the item e.g. series, video game, episode etc.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: CreativeWorkSeason, Episode, MediaObject, Movie, MovieSeries, RadioSeries, TVSeries, VideoGameSeries

内容的主题。: 商品的生产日期，例如车辆。
The date of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

内容的主题。: 该内容需要的熟练程度；期望值：“初学者”，“专家”。
Proficiency needed for this content; expected values: 'Beginner', 'Expert'.

内容的主题。: 常旅客，酒店忠诚度计划等的任何会员资格均适用于预订。
Any membership in a frequent flyer, hotel loyalty program, etc. being applied to the reservation.

内容的主题。: 提供会员资格的程序。
The program providing the membership.

内容的主题。: 参加该计划的前提条件。
Prerequisites for enrolling in the program.

内容的主题。: 教育或职业计划的类型。例如，教室，实习，交替等。
The type of educational or occupational program. For example, classroom, internship, alternance, etc..

内容的主题。: 计算机编程语言。
The computer programming language.

内容的主题。: 指示API是托管还是非托管。
Indicates whether API is managed or unmanaged.

内容的主题。: 属性所代表的特性的常用标识符，例如制造商或财产的标准代码。 propertyID可以是（1）前缀字符串，主要用于与产品属性标准一起使用； （2）特定于站点的非前缀字符串（例如，属性的主键或属性的供应商特定的ID），或（3）指示属性类型的URL，该URL指向外部词汇表，或描述该属性的Web资源（例如，词汇表条目）。Standards主体应从其标准中提升属性标识符的标准前缀。
A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be(1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific id of the property), or (3)a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property (e.g. a glossary entry).Standards bodies should promote a standard prefix for the identifiers of properties from their standards.

内容的主题。: 饮食计划的专有名称，通常由其制定者或创建者指定。
Proprietary name given to the diet plan, typically by its originator or creator.

内容的主题。: 蛋白质的克数。
The number of grams of protein.

内容的主题。: 服务提供者，服务运营者或服务执行者；商品生产者。另一方（卖方）可以代表提供商提供这些服务或商品。提供者也可以充当卖方。
