内容的主题。: 无论是在可用的物理空间还是在法律规定的限制方面，可以坐下的人数（例如，在车辆中）典型单位代码：C62
The number of persons that can be seated (e.g. in a vehicle), both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.Typical unit code(s): C62 for persons

内容的主题。: 座位的类型/类别。
The type/class of the seat.

内容的主题。: 一种预防性疗法，用于防止疾病最初发作后再次发生。
A preventative therapy used to prevent reoccurrence of the medical condition after an initial episode of the condition.

内容的主题。: 对作业的任何安全检查要求的描述。
A description of any security clearance requirements of the job.

内容的主题。: 乘客接受的安全检查的类型。
The type of security screening the passenger is subject to.

内容的主题。: 指向组织或个人寻求的产品或服务的指针（需求）。
A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

内容的主题。: 提供（出售/租赁/借出/借出）服务/商品的实体。卖方也可以是提供者。
An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

内容的主题。: 参与者的子属性。动作发送端的参与者。
A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the sending end of the action.

内容的主题。: 对工作所需的任何感官要求和水平的描述，包括听力和视觉。可以使用诸如O * net中的已定义术语，但是请注意，使用已定义术语时，无法指定能力级别及其性质。
A description of any sensory requirements and levels necessary to function on the job, including hearing and vision. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

内容的主题。: 输入和发送信息到大脑或脊髓的神经系统途径扩展。
The neurological pathway extension that inputs and sends information to the brain or spinal cord.

内容的主题。: 特定产品的序列号或任何字母数字标识符。当附加到要约时，它是要约中包含的产品序列号的快捷方式。
The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

内容的主题。: 该疗法可能引起的严重并发症和/或严重副作用。严重的不良后果包括危及生命的后果；导致死亡，伤残或永久损坏；需要住院或延长现有住院时间；导致先天性异常或出生缺陷；或危害患者，可能需要进行医学或手术干预以防止此定义中的结果之一。
A possible serious complication and/or serious side effect of this therapy. Serious adverse outcomes include those that are life-threatening; result in death, disability, or permanent damage; require hospitalization or prolong existing hospitalization; cause congenital anomalies or birth defects; or jeopardize the patient and may require medical or surgical intervention to prevent one of the outcomes in this definition.

内容的主题。: 游戏服务器的状态。
Status of a game server.

内容的主题。: 餐厅的美食。
The cuisine of the restaurant.

内容的主题。: 提供服务的地理区域。
The geographic area where the service is provided.

内容的主题。: 有资格使用此服务的受众。
The audience eligible for this service.

内容的主题。: 一个人可以访问该服务的位置（例如，公民结构，当地企业等）。
The location (e.g. civic structure, local business, etc.) where a person can go to access the service.

内容的主题。: 运营组织（如果与提供者不同）。 这样就可以表示组织提供的服务，但可以由另一个组织（如分包商）运营。
The operating organization, if different from the provider.  This enables the representation of services that are provided by an organization, but operated by another organization like a subcontractor.

内容的主题。: 服务产生的有形事物，例如 护照，许可证等
The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

内容的主题。: 用于访问服务的电话号码。
The phone number to use to access the service.

内容的主题。: 通过邮件访问服务的地址。
The address for accessing the service by mail.

内容的主题。: 通过短信访问服务的号码。
The number to access the service by text message.

内容的主题。: 提供的服务类型，例如 退伍军人的福利，紧急救济等
The type of service being offered, e.g. veterans' benefits, emergency relief, etc.

内容的主题。: 访问服务的网站。
The website to access the service.

内容的主题。: 份量，以体积或质量数表示。
The serving size, in terms of the number of volume or mass.

内容的主题。: 在此发布中共享的CreativeWork，例如图像，视频或音频剪辑。
A CreativeWork such as an image, video, or audio clip shared as part of this posting.

内容的主题。: 指示（可能有多个）运输目的地。 这些可以通过几种方式定义，例如 postalCode范围。
indicates (possibly multiple) shipping destinations. These can be defined in several ways e.g. postalCode ranges.

内容的主题。: 指示有关与要约相关的送货政策和选项的信息。
Indicates information about the shipping policies and options associated with an Offer.

内容的主题。: 标签，以将OfferShippingDetails与ShippingRateSettings匹配（在shippingSettingsLink交叉引用的上下文中）。
Label to match an OfferShippingDetails with a ShippingRateSettings (within the context of a shippingSettingsLink cross-reference).

内容的主题。: 运费是运送到指定目的地的费用。 通常，maxValue和货币值（MonetaryAmount的值）最合适。
The shipping rate is the cost of shipping to the specified destination. Typically, the maxValue and currency values (of the MonetaryAmount) are most appropriate.

内容的主题。: 链接到包含ShippingRateSettings和DeliveryTimeSettings详细信息的页面。
Link to a page containing ShippingRateSettings and DeliveryTimeSettings details.

内容的主题。: 一个人的兄弟姐妹。
A sibling of the person.

内容的主题。: 一个人的兄弟姐妹。
A sibling of the person.

内容的主题。: 测试检测到的迹象。
A sign detected by the test.

内容的主题。: 这种情况的迹象或症状。 迹象是医学状况的客观或身体可观察的表现，而症状是医学状况的主观经验。
A sign or symptom of this condition. Signs are objective or physically observable manifestations of the medical condition while symptoms are the subjective experience of the medical condition.

内容的主题。: 与浅层解剖相关的意义； 例如，浅层解剖结构的特征如何暗示潜在的医学状况或治疗过程。
The significance associated with the superficial anatomy; as an example, how characteristics of the superficial anatomy can suggest underlying medical conditions or courses of treatment.

内容的主题。: 页面上更重要的URL之一。 通常，这些是点击次数最多的非导航链接。
One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

内容的主题。: 页面上最重要的URL。 通常，这些是点击次数最多的非导航链接。
The most significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

内容的主题。: 知识，技能，能力，任务或任何其他主张的陈述，表达履行或担任此职务所需或要求的能力。
A statement of knowledge, skill, ability, task or any other assertion expressing a competency that is desired or required to fulfill this role or to work in this occupation.

内容的主题。: 库存单位（SKU），即产品或服务或要价所指产品的特定于商家的标识符。
The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

内容的主题。: 与项目相关的口号或座右铭。
A slogan or motto associated with the item.

内容的主题。: 指示是否允许在该场所吸烟，例如 在餐厅，旅馆或旅馆房间中。
Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.

内容的主题。: 钠的毫克数。
The number of milligrams of sodium.

内容的主题。: 软件应用程序的其他内容。
Additional content for a software application.

内容的主题。: 软件应用程序帮助。
Software application help.

内容的主题。: 应用程序的组件依赖性要求。这包括运行时环境和共享库，这些运行时环境和共享库未包含在应用程序分发包中，但它们是运行应用程序所必需的（示例：DirectX，Java或.NET运行时）。
Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (Examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

内容的主题。: 软件实例的版本。
Version of the software instance.

内容的主题。: 创建者代表其工作的组织。
The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

内容的主题。: 起源神经元的神经通路。
The neurological pathway that originates the neurons.

内容的主题。: 当不知道更具体的属性（例如locationCreated，spatialCoverage，contentLocation）合适时，可以使用“ spatial”属性。
The "spatial" property can be used in cases when more specific properties(e.g. locationCreated, spatialCoverage, contentLocation) are not known to be appropriate.

内容的主题。: CreativeWork的spatialCoverage指示作为内容焦点的位置。它是contentLocation的子属性，主要用于获得更多技术和详细材料。例如，使用数据集，它指示数据集描述的区域：纽约天气的数据集将具有spaceCoverage，该空间为位置：纽约州。
The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of      contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates      areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

内容的主题。: 表示网页中特别突出的部分，即被突出显示为特别适用于文本到语音转换的部分。页面的其他部分在特定情况下也可能有用。 “ speakable”属性用于指示最有可能对语音有用的部分。“ speakable”属性可以重复任意次数，并具有三种可能的“ content-locator”值：1。）id-value URL引用-使用要注释的页面中元素的id值。可以说的最简单的用法是具有（可能是相对的）URL值，引用相关文档的已标识部分。2。CSS选择器-在带注释的页面中处理内容，例如。通过类属性。使用cssSelector属性。3.）XPaths-通过XPaths寻址内容（假定内容的XML视图）。使用xpath属性，除了简单的ID引用之外，对于可说出的部分的更复杂的标记，可以使用CSS选择器或XPath表达式来选择可说出的文档部分。为此，我们定义了一种支持类型SpeakableSpecification，它被定义为可发音属性的可能值。
Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech.The speakable property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values:1.) id-value URL references - uses id-value of an element in the page being annotated. The simplest use of speakable has (potentially relative) URL values, referencing identified sections of the document concerned.2.) CSS Selectors - addresses content in the annotated page, eg. via class attribute. Use the cssSelector property.3.)  XPaths - addresses content via XPaths (assuming an XML view of the content). Use the xpath property.For more sophisticated markup of speakable sections beyond simple ID references, either CSS selectors or XPath expressions to pick out document section(s) as speakable. For thiswe define a supporting type, SpeakableSpecification  which is defined to be a possible value of the speakable property.

内容的主题。: 与该职位发布相关的任何特殊承诺。有效条目包括VeteranCommit，MilitarySpouseCommit等。
Any special commitments associated with this job posting. Valid entries include VeteranCommit, MilitarySpouseCommit, etc.

内容的主题。: 某个特定地点的特殊开放时间，使用它来显式覆盖由openHoursSpecification或openHours带入范围的一般开放时间。
The special opening hours of a certain place.Use this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by openingHoursSpecification or openingHours.

内容的主题。: 该网页内容所适用的领域专业之一。
One of the domain specialities to which this web page's content applies.

内容的主题。: 使用的标记形式。例如。 SSML或IPA。
Form of markup used. eg. SSML or IPA.

内容的主题。: 车辆的速度范围。如果车辆由发动机提供动力，则速度范围的上限（以maxValue表示应为常规条件下可达到的最大速度）。典型单位代码：KMH为km / h，HM为每小时英里（0.447 04 m / s），KNT为打结*注1：使用minValue和maxValue表示范围。通常，最小值为零。*注2：测量速度范围的方法有很多。可以链接到信息有关如何使用valueReference属性确定给定值的信息。
The speed range of the vehicle. If the vehicle is powered by an engine, the upper limit of the speed range (indicated by maxValue should be the maximum speed achievable under regular conditions.Typical unit code(s): KMH for km/h, HM for mile per hour (0.447 04 m/s), KNT for knot*Note 1: Use minValue and maxValue to indicate the range. Typically, the minimal value is zero.* Note 2: There are many different ways of measuring the speed range. You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the valueReference property.

内容的主题。: 在包含的CreativeWork中引用该报价的（例如，虚构的）字符，人物或组织。
The (e.g. fictional) character, Person or Organization to whom the quotation is attributed within the containing CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 通过认捐，承诺或财政捐助来支持事物的人或组织。例如医学研究的赞助商或活动的公司赞助商。
A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: CreativeWork, Event, Grant, MedicalStudy, Organization, Person

内容的主题。: 一种运动（例如棒球）。
A type of sport (e.g. Baseball).

内容的主题。: 位置的子属性。发生此动作的体育活动位置。
A sub property of location. The sports activity location where this action occurred.

内容的主题。: 位置的子属性。发生此动作的体育赛事。
A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.

内容的主题。: 参与者的子属性。参加这项运动的运动队。
A sub property of participant. The sports team that participated on this action.

内容的主题。: 该人的配偶。
The person's spouse.

内容的主题。: 条件的阶段（如果适用）。
The stage of the condition, if applicable.

内容的主题。: 以数字表示的阶段，例如3。
The stage represented as a number, e.g. 3.

内容的主题。: 旅馆业或食品店的官方评级，例如来自国家协会或标准机构。使用author属性指示评分单位，例如作为组织的名称，例如（HOTREC，DEHOGA，WHR或Hotelstars）。
An official rating for a lodging business or food establishment, e.g. from national associations or standards bodies. Use the author property to indicate the rating organization, e.g. as an Organization with name such as (e.g. HOTREC, DEHOGA, WHR, or Hotelstars).

内容的主题。: 项目的开始日期和时间（采用ISO 8601日期格式）。
The start date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: CreativeWorkSeason, CreativeWorkSeries, DatedMoneySpecification, EducationalOccupationalProgram, Event, Role, Schedule

内容的主题。: 剪辑的开始时间表示为从工作开始起的秒数。
The start time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

内容的主题。: 某物的开始时间。对于保留的事件或服务（例如，Food EstablishmentmentReservation），预计将开始的时间。对于跨越一段时间的操作，执行操作的时间。例如约翰从一月到十二月写了一本书。对于包括音频和视频在内的媒体，它是一个较大文件中剪辑开始的时间偏移。请注意，即使使用时间描述日期，Event也使用startDate / endDate而不是startTime / endTime。在将来的修订版中可能会澄清这种情况。
The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to December. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the start of a clip within a larger file.Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

内容的主题。: 研究状态（枚举）。
The status of the study (enumerated).

内容的主题。: 方向盘或类似设备（主要用于汽车）的位置。
The position of the steering wheel or similar device (mostly for cars).

内容的主题。: 单个步骤项（如HowToStep，文本，文档，视频等）或HowToSection。
A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection.

内容的主题。: stepValue属性指示PropertyValueSpecification中值的预期（和必需）粒度。
The stepValue attribute indicates the granularity that is expected (and required) of the value in a PropertyValueSpecification.

内容的主题。: 单个步骤项（如HowToStep，文本，文档，视频等）或HowToSection（最初误命名为“步骤”；首选为“步骤”）。
A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection (originally misnamed 'steps'; 'step' is preferred).

内容的主题。: 存储要求（需要可用空间）。
Storage requirements (free space required).

内容的主题。: 街道地址。 例如，1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy。
The street address. For example, 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy.

内容的主题。: 活性成分强度的单位，例如 毫克
The units of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. mg.

内容的主题。: 活性成分强度的值，例如 325。
The value of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. 325.

内容的主题。: 骨骼之间如何物理连接的名称。
The name given to how bone physically connects to each other.

内容的主题。: 与该实体相关的医学研究或试验。
A medical study or trial related to this entity.

内容的主题。: 有关观察性研究设计的细节（枚举）。
Specifics about the observational study design (enumerated).

内容的主题。: 研究进行/进行的位置。
The location in which the study is taking/took place.

内容的主题。: 研究对象，即研究对象所研究的医学状况，疗法，设备，药物等之一。
A subject of the study, i.e. one of the medical conditions, therapies, devices, drugs, etc. investigated by the study.

内容的主题。: 仅用于测试。
This is a StupidProperty! - for testing only

内容的主题。: 属于此事件的事件。例如，会议事件包括许多演示，每个演示都是会议的子事件。
An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

内容的主题。: 属于此事件的事件。例如，会议事件包括许多演示，会议的每个子事件。
Events that are a part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each subEvents of the conference.

内容的主题。: 两个组织之间的关系，其中第一个包括第二个组织，例如作为子公司。另请参阅：更具体的“部门”属性。
A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

内容的主题。: 包装中包含单独的预订。通常是重复属性。
The individual reservations included in the package. Typically a repeated property.

内容的主题。: 子阶段，例如IIIa阶段为“ a”。
The substage, e.g. 'a' for Stage IIIa.

内容的主题。: 组成此解剖结构的（子）结构。
Component (sub-)structure(s) that comprise this anatomical structure.

内容的主题。: 面板的组件测试。
A component test of the panel.

内容的主题。: 标识属于此行程的子行程的行程。例如，多日行程的第1天，第2天等。
Identifies a Trip that is a subTrip of this Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

内容的主题。: 关于此事的创造性工作或活动。
A CreativeWork or Event about this Thing.

内容的主题。: 提供IETF BCP 47标准格式的字幕/字幕的语言。
Languages in which subtitles/captions are available, in IETF BCP 47 standard format.

内容的主题。: 从产品的较新版本到先前（通常是已停产）的指针。
A pointer from a newer variant of a product  to its previous, often discontinued predecessor.

内容的主题。: 糖克数。
The number of grams of sugar.

内容的主题。: 问题的答案（可能是几个答案之一，可能是错误的）在问题/答案站点上。
An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

内容的主题。: 个人或听众的性别。
The gender of the person or audience.

内容的主题。: 建议观看内容的最大年龄。
Maximal age recommended for viewing content.

内容的主题。: 建议最低年龄，以查看内容。
Minimal age recommended for viewing content.

内容的主题。: 表示适合此食谱或菜单项的饮食限制或准则，例如糖尿病，清真等
Indicates a dietary restriction or guideline for which this recipe or menu item is suitable, e.g. diabetic, halal etc.

内容的主题。: 此事件所属的事件。例如，单个音乐表演的集合可能每个都有一个音乐节作为其SuperEvent。
An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

内容的主题。: 将术语（即属性，类或枚举）与取代它的术语相关联。
Relates a term (i.e. a property, class or enumeration) to one that supersedes it.

内容的主题。: 仪器的子属性。执行指令或指示时消耗的耗材。
A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.

内容的主题。: 动脉供血的区域。
The area to which the artery supplies blood.

内容的主题。: SoftwareApplication的支持数据。
Supporting data for a SoftwareApplication.

内容的主题。: 在某些艺术品中用作表面的材料，例如帆布，纸张，木材，木板等
A material used as a surface in some artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

内容的主题。: 指示操作的目标EntryPoint。
Indicates a target EntryPoint for an Action.

内容的主题。: 对象的子属性。动作的收集目标。
A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

内容的主题。: 在已建立的教育框架中对节点的描述。
The description of a node in an established educational framework.

内容的主题。: 已建立的教育框架中节点的名称。
The name of a node in an established educational framework.

内容的主题。: 应用开发类型：电话，Metro风格，桌面，XBox等。
Type of app development: phone, Metro style, desktop, XBox, etc.

内容的主题。: 预期或通常使用的人群的特征，例如“成人”。
Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

内容的主题。: 代码适用的目标操作系统/产品。如果适用于多个版本，则只能使用产品名称。
Target Operating System / Product to which the code applies.  If applies to several versions, just the product name can be used.

内容的主题。: 已建立的教育框架中节点的URL。
The URL of a node in an established educational framework.

内容的主题。: 组织或个人的税号/财务ID，例如美国的TIN或西班牙的CIF / NIF。
The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

内容的主题。: 所描述的项目旨在帮助一个人学习由参考术语定义的能力或学习成果。
The item being described is intended to help a person learn the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

内容的主题。: 电话号码。
The telephone number.

内容的主题。: 在不知道更具体的属性（例如，temporalCoverage，dateCreated，dateModified，datePublished）合适的情况下，可以使用“ temporal”属性。
The "temporal" property can be used in cases where more specific properties(e.g. temporalCoverage, dateCreated, dateModified, datePublished) are not known to be appropriate.

内容的主题。: CreativeWork的temporalCoverage指示内容所适用的时间段，即它描述为DateTime或文本字符串，以ISO 8601时间间隔格式表示时间段。在数据集的情况下，通常会以精确的符号表示相关的时间段（例如，对于2011年的人口普查数据集，2011年将写为“ 2011/2012”）。其他形式的内容，例如ScholarlyArticle，Book，TVSeries或TVEpisode可能会以更广泛的方式（通过文字形式或通过众所周知的URL）指示其temporalCoverage。诸如书籍之类的书面作品有时也可能具有精确的时间范围，例如在1939年至1945年设定的作品可以通过“ 1939/1945”以ISO 8601间隔格式表示。开放式日期范围可以用“ ..”代替结束日期。例如，“ 2015-11 / ..”表示从2015年11月开始且没有指定最终日期的范围。这是暂时的，将来可能会在ISO 8601正式更新时进行更新。
The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in ISO 8601 time interval format. In      the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL.      Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".Open-ended date ranges can be written with ".." in place of the end date. For example, "2015-11/.." indicates a range beginning in November 2015 and with no specified final date. This is tentative and might be updated in future when ISO 8601 is officially updated.

内容的主题。: 在DefinedTermSet中标识此DefinedTerm的代码
A code that identifies this DefinedTerm within a DefinedTermSet

内容的主题。: 机构定义的学期中的时间量。学期是学生上一堂或多堂课的时间长度。学期和季度是学期的常用单位。
The amount of time in a term as defined by the institution. A term is a length of time where students take one or more classes. Semesters and quarters are common units for term.

内容的主题。: 易于阅读的服务条款文档。
Human-readable terms of service documentation.

内容的主题。: 每年提供学习条款的次数。学期和季度是学期的常用单位。例如，如果学生在一年内只能学习2个学期的课程，则termPerYear应该为2。
The number of times terms of study are offered per year. Semesters and quarters are common units for term. For example, if the student can only take 2 semesters for the program in one year, then termsPerYear should be 2.

内容的主题。: 此CreativeWork的文本内容。
The textual content of this CreativeWork.

内容的主题。: 带有注释的文本值。
Text value being annotated.

内容的主题。: 图片或视频的缩略图。
Thumbnail image for an image or video.

内容的主题。: 与事物相关的缩略图。
A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

内容的主题。: 与公司对象关联的交易所交易工具。 tickerSymbol表示为交易所和指令名称，用空格字符分隔。对于tickerSymbol属性的交换组件，建议使用ISO15022中指定的市场标识符代码（MIC）的受控词汇表。
The exchange traded instrument associated with a Corporation object. The tickerSymbol is expressed as an exchange and an instrument name separated by a space character. For the exchange component of the tickerSymbol attribute, we recommend using the controlled vocabulary of Market Identifier Codes (MIC) specified in ISO15022.

内容的主题。: 票证的唯一标识符。
The unique identifier for the ticket.

内容的主题。: 对可用于入口的资产（例如条形码，QR码图像或PDF）的引用。
Reference to an asset (e.g., Barcode, QR code image or PDF) usable for entrance.

内容的主题。: 与票证关联的座位。
The seat associated with the ticket.

内容的主题。: 程序正常运行的时间。例如，“晚上”。
The time of day the program normally runs. For example, "evenings".

内容的主题。: 对于典型的预期目标受众，使用或通过此学习资源工作所需的大概或典型时间。 'PT30M'，'PT1H25M'。
Approximate or typical time it takes to work with or through this learning resource for the typical intended target audience, e.g. 'PT30M', 'PT1H25M'.

内容的主题。: 如果参加全日制，则完成该计划的预期时间。
The expected length of time to complete the program if attending full-time.

内容的主题。: 测试所需的组织样本类型。
The type of tissue sample required for the test.

内容的主题。: 职位名称。
The title of the job.

内容的主题。: 代表电影或电视作品最一般/抽象级别的EIDR（娱乐标识符注册表）标识符。例如，被称为“捉鬼敢死队”的电影的标题EIDR为“ 10.5240 / 7EC7-228A-510A-053E- CBB8-J”。该标题（或作品）可能有几种变体，EIDR将其称为“编辑”。请参阅editEIDR。由于诸如Movie和TVEpisode之类的schema.org类型可用于作品及其多种表达方式，因此可以单独使用titleEIDR（作为一般说明），或与editEIDR一起使用以进行更具体的编辑。
An EIDR (Entertainment Identifier Registry) identifier representing at the most general/abstract level, a work of film or television.For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" has a titleEIDR of  "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J". This title (or work) may have several variants, which EIDR calls "edits". See editEIDR.Since schema.org types like Movie and TVEpisode can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possible to use titleEIDR alone (for a general description), or alongside editEIDR for a more edit-specific description.

内容的主题。: 位置的子属性。操作后对象或代理的最终位置。
A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

内容的主题。: 收件人的子属性。直接发送邮件的收件人。
A sub property of recipient. The recipient who was directly sent the message.

内容的主题。: 挂在车辆上的拖车的允许垂直载荷（TWR）。也称为舌头额定载荷（TLR）或垂直额定载荷（VLR）典型单位代码：千克的KGM，磅的LBR注1：您可以在QuantitativeValue节点的名称中指示其他信息。注2：您可以也可以链接到使用valueReference提供其他信息的QualitativeValue节点。注3：请注意，可以使用minValue和maxValue指示范围。
The permitted vertical load (TWR) of a trailer attached to the vehicle. Also referred to as Tongue Load Rating (TLR) or Vertical Load Rating (VLR)Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for poundNote 1: You can indicate additional information in the name of the QuantitativeValue node.Note 2: You may also link to a QualitativeValue node that provides additional information using valueReference.Note 3: Note that you can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.

内容的主题。: 仪器的子属性。执行指令或指示时使用（但不消耗）的对象。
A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.

内容的主题。: 车辆发动机的扭矩（转向力）典型单位代码：牛顿米（N m）的NU，牛顿米的英尺/英尺的F17或牛顿米的英寸/英寸的F48注1：您可以链接到信息有关如何使用valueReference属性确定给定值（例如参考RPM）的说明。注2：可以使用minValue和maxValue指示范围。
The torque (turning force) of the vehicle's engine.Typical unit code(s): NU for newton metre (N m), F17 for pound-force per foot, or F48 for pound-force per inchNote 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined (e.g. reference RPM) using the valueReference property.Note 2: You can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.

内容的主题。: 此职位发布的空缺职位数。使用正整数。如果职位数量不清楚或未知，请不要使用。
The number of positions open for this job posting. Use a positive integer. Do not use if the number of positions is unclear or not known.

内容的主题。: 应付总额。
The total amount due.

内容的主题。: 预订或机票的总价，包括适用的税费，运费等使用指南：使用值从0123456789（Unicode'DIGIT ZERO'（U + 0030）到'DIGIT NINE'（U + 0039）），而不是表面上类似的值Unicode符号。使用“。” （Unicode'FULL STOP'（U + 002E））而不是'，'表示小数点。避免将这些符号用作可读性分隔符。
The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.Usage guidelines:Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

内容的主题。: 执行指令或指示所需的总时间（包括准备耗材的时间），以ISO 8601持续时间格式表示。
The total time required to perform instructions or a direction (including time to prepare the supplies), in ISO 8601 duration format.

内容的主题。: 该页面提供有关如何预订某个地方的旅游信息的页面，例如房地产环境中的Accommodation或ApartmentComplex以及其他适当类型的旅游。
A page providing information on how to book a tour of some Place, such as an Accommodation or ApartmentComplex in a real estate setting, as well as other kinds of tours as appropriate.

内容的主题。: 适合游客类型的景点。例如。儿童，来自特定国家/地区的访客等
Attraction suitable for type(s) of tourist. eg. Children, visitors from a particular country, etc.

内容的主题。: 音乐录制（曲目）：通常是一首歌曲。如果给出了ItemList，则列表应包含MusicRecording类型的项目。
A music recording (track): usually a single song. If an ItemList is given, the list should contain items of type MusicRecording.

内容的主题。: 托运人跟踪号。
Shipper tracking number.

内容的主题。: 包裹投递的追踪网址。
Tracking url for the parcel delivery.

内容的主题。: 音乐录制（曲目）：通常是一首歌曲。
A music recording (track): usually a single song.

内容的主题。: 电影或电视/广播系列，季节，剧集等的预告片。
The trailer of a movie or tv/radio series, season, episode, etc.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: CreativeWorkSeason, Episode, Movie, MovieSeries, RadioSeries, TVSeries, VideoGame, VideoGameSeries

内容的主题。: 挂在车辆上的拖车的允许重量。典型单位代码：KGM表示千克，LBR表示磅*注1：您可以在QuantitativeValue节点的名称中指示其他信息。*注2：您也可以链接到使用valueReference提供附加信息的QualitativeValue节点。*注3：请注意，可以使用minValue和maxValue指示范围。
The permitted weight of a trailer attached to the vehicle.Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the name of the QuantitativeValue node.* Note 2: You may also link to a QualitativeValue node that provides additional information using valueReference.* Note 3: Note that you can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.

内容的主题。: 火车的名称（例如东方快车）。
The name of the train (e.g. The Orient Express).

内容的主题。: 火车的唯一标识符。
The unique identifier for the train.

内容的主题。: 在该计划中获得的估计薪水。
The estimated salary earned while in the program.

内容的主题。: 反式脂肪的克数。
The number of grams of trans fat.

内容的主题。: 如果此MediaObject是AudioObject或VideoObject，则为该对象的副本。
If this MediaObject is an AudioObject or VideoObject, the transcript of that object.

内容的主题。: 订单已发送到交货的典型延迟，货物到达最终客户。典型属性：minValue，maxValue，unitCode（d为DAY）。
The typical delay the order has been sent for delivery and the goods reach the final customer. Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY).

内容的主题。: 用于将OfferShippingDetails与DeliveryTimeSettings匹配的标签（在shippingSettingsLink交叉引用的上下文中）。
Label to match an OfferShippingDetails with a DeliveryTimeSettings (within the context of a shippingSettingsLink cross-reference).

内容的主题。: 该作品已被翻译自该作品。例如物种起源是“论物种起源”的翻译
The work that this work has been translated from. e.g. 物种起源 is a translationOf “On the Origin of Species”

内容的主题。: 使创意作品适应目标市场的不同语言，地区差异和技术要求的组织或人员，或在某个事件期间进行翻译的组织或人员。
Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

内容的主题。: 疾病如何通过途径或媒介传播，例如“直接接触”，“埃及伊蚊”等。
How the disease spreads, either as a route or vector, for example 'direct contact', 'Aedes aegypti', etc.

内容的主题。: 有关旅行禁令的信息，例如在大流行的情况下。
Information about travel bans, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

内容的主题。: 有关试验设计的细节（枚举）。
Specifics about the trial design (enumerated).

内容的主题。: 静脉流入的解剖或器官系统；静脉连接的较大结构。
The anatomical or organ system that the vein flows into; a larger structure that the vein connects to.

内容的主题。: BedDetail所引用的床的类型，即可用数量表示的床的类型（按数量表示）。
The type of bed to which the BedDetail refers, i.e. the type of bed available in the quantity indicated by quantity.

内容的主题。: 该结构化值所指的产品。
The product that this structured value is referring to.

内容的主题。: 典型的预期年龄范围，例如'7-9'，'11-'。
The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

内容的主题。: 全日制学生希望在1个学期中获得的学分或学分数量，但“学期”由院校定义。
The number of credits or units a full-time student would be expected to take in 1 term however 'term' is defined by the institution.

内容的主题。: 在这种情况下，通常会进行医学检查。
A medical test typically performed given this condition.

内容的主题。: 预订或票证所针对的个人或组织。
The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

内容的主题。: 使用UN / CEFACT通用代码（3个字符）或URL给出的度量单位。除UN / CEFACT通用代码外，其他代码也可以使用带前缀的冒号。
The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

内容的主题。: 指示度量单位的字符串或文本。如果您不能为unitCode提供标准的单位代码，则很有用。
A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

内容的主题。: 对于组织（通常是NewsMediaOrganization），有关使用未命名来源的政策和所需决策过程的声明。
For an Organization (typically a NewsMediaOrganization), a statement about policy on use of unnamed sources and the decision process required.

内容的主题。: 不饱和脂肪的克数。
The number of grams of unsaturated fat.

内容的主题。: 该媒体对象上载到此站点的日期。
Date when this media object was uploaded to this site.

内容的主题。: 从社区收到对此问题，答案或评论的支持数。
The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

内容的主题。: 商品的网址。
URL of the item.

内容的主题。: 网址模板（RFC6570），将用于构造操作执行目标。
An url template (RFC6570) that will be used to construct the target of the execution of the action.

内容的主题。: schema.org usageInfoproperty指示有关CreativeWork的更多信息。此属性适用于免费提供的作品以及需要付款或其他交易的作品。它可以引用其他信息，例如社区对首选链接和引用约定以及购买细节的期望。对于可以进行商业许可的产品，usageInfo可以提供有关许可选项的详细，特定于资源的信息。此属性可以与用于指示适用于某些内容的许可的license属性一起使用。 usageInfo属性可以提供有关其他许可选项的信息，例如获取图像的商业使用权，该图像也可以在非商业性知识共享许可下获得。
The schema.org usageInfoproperty indicates further information about a CreativeWork. This property is applicable both to works that are freely available and to those that require payment or other transactions. It can reference additional information e.g. community expectations on preferred linking and citation conventions, as well as purchasing details. For something that can be commercially licensed, usageInfo can provide detailed, resource-specific information about licensing options.This property can be used alongside the license property which indicates license(s) applicable to some piece of content. The usageInfo property can provide information about other licensing options, e.g. acquiring commercial usage rights for an image that is also available under non-commercial creative commons licenses.

内容的主题。: 测试用于诊断的条件。
A condition the test is used to diagnose.

内容的主题。: 使用WebSite或SoftwareApplication进行CreativeWork的交互次数。
The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication.

内容的主题。: 用于执行测试的设备。
Device used to perform the test.

内容的主题。: 解释计划ID的标准。优选的是“ HIOS”。有关更多详细信息，请参阅Medicare和Medicaid服务中心。
The standard for interpreting thePlan ID. The preferred is "HIOS". See the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services for more details.

内容的主题。: 许可证或类似物品的有效期限。
The duration of validity of a permit or similar thing.

内容的主题。: 项目生效的日期。
The date when the item becomes valid.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: Demand, LocationFeatureSpecification, MonetaryAmount, Offer, OpeningHoursSpecification, Permit, PriceSpecification

内容的主题。: 许可证或类似物品有效的地理区域。
The geographic area where a permit or similar thing is valid.

内容的主题。: 项目无效后的日期。例如，要约的结束，工资期或营业时间。
The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.
CommunicateAction, CreativeWork, Event: Demand, JobPosting, LocationFeatureSpecification, MonetaryAmount, Offer, OpeningHoursSpecification, PriceSpecification

内容的主题。: 该项目不再有效的日期。
The date when the item is no longer valid.

内容的主题。: 定量值或属性值节点的值。对于QuantitativeValue和MonetaryAmount，建议的值类型为“ Number”。对于PropertyValue，它可以为“ Text;”，“ Number”，“ Boolean”或“ StructuredValue”。使用从0123456789（Unicode'DIGIT ZERO'（U + 0030）到'DIGIT NINE'（U + 0039））的值，而不是表面上类似的Unicode符号。使用'。' （Unicode'FULL STOP'（U + 002E））而不是'，'表示小数点。避免将这些符号用作可读性分隔符。
The value of the quantitative value or property value node.For QuantitativeValue and MonetaryAmount, the recommended type for values is 'Number'.For PropertyValue, it can be 'Text;', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

内容的主题。: 指定价格规格中是否包含适用的增值税（VAT）。
Specifies whether the applicable value-added tax (VAT) is included in the price specification or not.

内容的主题。: 指定文字值中字符数的允许范围。
Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

内容的主题。: 指定文字值中字符数的最小允许范围。
Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

内容的主题。: 指示将以类似于HTML的input @ name的方式在URL模板和表单编码中使用的PropertyValueSpecification的名称。
Indicates the name of the PropertyValueSpecification to be used in URL templates and form encoding in a manner analogous to HTML's input@name.

内容的主题。: 指定用于根据HTML规范测试文字值的正则表达式。
Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

内容的主题。: 指向辅助值的指针，该值可提供有关原始值的其他信息，例如参考温度。
A pointer to a secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature.

内容的主题。: 是否必须填写属性才能完成操作。默认为false。
Whether the property must be filled in to complete the action.  Default is false.

内容的主题。: variableMeasured属性可以指示（必要时重复）在某些数据集中测量的变量，这些变量描述为文本或使用PropertyValue描述为标识符和描述对。
The variableMeasured property can indicate (repeated as necessary) the  variables that are measured in some dataset, either described as text or as pairs of identifier and description using PropertyValue.

内容的主题。: 最初命名为variablesMeasured，variableMeasured属性可以指示（必要时重复）在某些数据集中测量的变量，这些变量描述为文本或使用PropertyValue描述为标识符和描述对。
Originally named variablesMeasured, The variableMeasured property can indicate (repeated as necessary) the  variables that are measured in some dataset, either described as text or as pairs of identifier and description using PropertyValue.

内容的主题。: 如果问题是印刷变体，请对该问题的变体封面进行说明。例如，“ Bryan Hitch变式封面”或“第二印刷变式”。
A description of the variant cover    for the issue, if the issue is a variant printing. For example, "Bryan Hitch    Variant Cover" or "2nd Printing Variant".

内容的主题。: 组织或个人的增值税ID。
The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

内容的主题。: 指示车辆配置的短文本，例如'5dr掀背车ST 2.5 MT 225 hp'或'限量版'。
A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

内容的主题。: 有关车辆的一个或多个引擎的信息。
Information about the engine or engines of the vehicle.

内容的主题。: 车辆识别号（VIN）是汽车行业用于识别单个机动车的唯一序列号。
The Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) is a unique serial number used by the automotive industry to identify individual motor vehicles.

内容的主题。: 车辆内部的颜色或颜色组合。
The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

内容的主题。: 车辆内部的类型或材料（例如合成纤维，皮革，木材等）。尽管大多数内饰类型的特征在于所使用的材料，但内饰类型也可以基于车辆的使用或目标受众。
The type or material of the interior of the vehicle (e.g. synthetic fabric, leather, wood, etc.). While most interior types are characterized by the material used, an interior type can also be based on vehicle usage or target audience.

内容的主题。: 车辆模型的发布日期（通常用于区分同一品牌和型号的版本）。
The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

内容的主题。: 无论是在可用的物理空间还是在法律规定的限制方面，可以坐在车辆上的乘客人数。典型单位代码：C62。
The number of passengers that can be seated in the vehicle, both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.Typical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

内容的主题。: 指示车辆是否已用于特殊目的，例如商业租赁，驾驶学校或作为出租车。许多国家/地区的立法要求在出售汽车时必须披露这些信息。
Indicates whether the vehicle has been used for special purposes, like commercial rental, driving school, or as a taxi. The legislation in many countries requires this information to be revealed when offering a car for sale.

内容的主题。: 用于将动力从旋转动力源传递到车轮或其他相关组件的组件类型（汽车的“变​​速箱”）。
The type of component used for transmitting the power from a rotating power source to the wheels or other relevant component(s) ("gearbox" for cars).

内容的主题。: “供应商”是“卖方”的较早术语。
'vendor' is an earlier term for 'seller'.

内容的主题。: 披露有关NewsMediaOrganization或其他事实检查组织的验证和事实检查过程。
Disclosure about verification and fact-checking processes for a NewsMediaOrganization or other fact-checking Organization.

内容的主题。: 由指定资源体现的CreativeWork版本。
The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

内容的主题。: 嵌入式视频对象。
An embedded video object.

内容的主题。: 所使用的放映或视频广播的类型（例如IMAX，3D，SD，HD等）。
The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

内容的主题。: 视频的帧大小。
The frame size of the video.

内容的主题。: 视频的质量。
The quality of the video.

内容的主题。: 确定出版物或多部分作品的数量；例如“ iii”或“ 2”。
Identifies the volume of publication or multi-part work; for example, "iii" or "2".

内容的主题。: 有关该药物的任何FDA或其他警告（文本或URL）。
Any FDA or other warnings about the drug (text or URL).

内容的主题。: 要约中包含的保修承诺。
The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

内容的主题。: 要约中包含的保修承诺。
The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

内容的主题。: 保修承诺的范围。
The scope of the warranty promise.

内容的主题。: 旅客可以在线登机的时间。
The time when a passenger can check into the flight online.

内容的主题。: 供稿的网址，例如与播客系列，博客或一系列带日期戳的更新相关联。通常是RSS或Atom。
The URL for a feed, e.g. associated with a podcast series, blog, or series of date-stamped updates. This is usually RSS or Atom.

内容的主题。: 产品或人的体重。
The weight of the product or person.

内容的主题。: 允许的已装载车辆的总重量，包括乘客和货物以及空车的重量。典型单位代码：KGM表示公斤，LBR表示磅注1：您可以在QuantitativeValue节点的名称中指示其他信息。注意2：您也可以使用valueReference链接到提供其他信息的QualitativeValue节点。注意3：请注意，您可以使用minValue和maxValue来指示范围。
The permitted total weight of the loaded vehicle, including passengers and cargo and the weight of the empty vehicle.Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for poundNote 1: You can indicate additional information in the name of the QuantitativeValue node.Note 2: You may also link to a QualitativeValue node that provides additional information using valueReference.Note 3: Note that you can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.

内容的主题。: 前轮和后轮中心之间的距离。典型单位代码：CMT表示厘米，MTR表示米，INH表示英寸，FOT表示脚/脚
The distance between the centers of the front and rear wheels.Typical unit code(s): CMT for centimeters, MTR for meters, INH for inches, FOT for foot/feet

内容的主题。: 项目的宽度。
The width of the item.

内容的主题。: 参与者的子属性。动作的获胜者。
A sub property of participant. The winner of the action.

内容的主题。: 该条文本中的字数。
The number of words in the text of the Article.

内容的主题。: 本创意作品的示例/实例/实现/派生。例如。平装版，第一版或eBook。
Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. eg. The paperback edition, first edition, or eBook.

内容的主题。: 某些活动中的特色作品，例如在ExhibitionEvent中展出。特定的子属性可用于workPerformed（例如，戏剧）或workPresented（在ScreeningEvent上的电影）。
A work featured in some event, e.g. exhibited in an ExhibitionEvent.       Specific subproperties are available for workPerformed (e.g. a play), or a workPresented (a Movie at a ScreeningEvent).

内容的主题。: 该工作的典型工作时间（例如，第一班，夜班，上午8点至下午5点）。
The typical working hours for this job (e.g. 1st shift, night shift, 8am-5pm).

内容的主题。: 一个人的工作地点的联系位置。
A contact location for a person's place of work.

内容的主题。: 在某些事件中进行的工作，例如在TheaterEvent中进行的戏剧。
A work performed in some event, for example a play performed in a TheaterEvent.

内容的主题。: 活动期间放映的电影。
The movie presented during this event.

内容的主题。: 作品是该作品内容的翻译。例如西游记的英文译本为“西游记”，德语的译本为“ Monkeys Pilgerfahrt”，越南语译本为Tâydukýbìnhkhảo。
A work that is a translation of the content of this work. e.g. 西遊記 has an English workTranslation “Journey to the West”,a German workTranslation “Monkeys Pilgerfahrt” and a Vietnamese  translation Tây du ký bình khảo.

内容的主题。: 运动的生理输出的定量测量；也称为能源支出。
Quantitative measure of the physiologic output of the exercise; also referred to as energy expenditure.

内容的主题。: 此人工作的组织。
Organizations that the person works for.

内容的主题。: 此评级系统中允许的最低值。 如果忽略最差评分，则假定为1。
The lowest value allowed in this rating system. If worstRating is omitted, 1 is assumed.

内容的主题。: XPath，例如 SpeakableSpecification或WebPageElement。 在后一种情况下，页面内的多个匹配项可以构成一个概念上的“网页元素”。
An XPath, e.g. of a SpeakableSpecification or WebPageElement. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

内容的主题。: 建造年份。 这对应于RESO中的YearBuilt字段。
The year an Accommodation was constructed. This corresponds to the YearBuilt field in RESO.

内容的主题。: 该企业的年收入规模。
The size of the business in annual revenue.

内容的主题。: 公司的年龄。
The age of the business.

内容的主题。: 通过执行指令得到的数量。 例如，一架纸飞机，10支个性化蜡烛。
The quantity that results by performing instructions. For example, a paper airplane, 10 personalized candles.
